Aramane ( Kannada : ಅರಮನೆ , translation : Palace ) is a 2008 Indian Kannada drama film directed by Nagashekhar , starring Ganesh and Anant Nag in the lead roles .
National Lampoon 's Vacation , sometimes referred to as Vacation , is a 1983 American comedy film directed by Harold Ramis and starring Chevy Chase , Beverly D'Angelo , Randy Quaid , Dana Barron , and Anthony Michael Hall .
The Adventures of Captain Africa ( 1955 ) is a Columbia serial starring John Hart .
Shaolin Plot ( Chinese : 四大門派 ) is a 1977 Hong Kong film directed by Huang Feng and featuring Sammo Hung in his first starring role and as action director .

The Case of the Velvet Claws is a 1936 mystery film , based on the first Perry Mason novel by Erle Stanley Gardner and featuring the fourth and final appearance of Warren William as defense attorney Mason .

Justice of the Wild is a 1913 American silent short adventure film directed by Frank E. Montgomery starring Harry Van Meter , Mona Darkfeather , and Jack Messick .

The Muppets Take Manhattan is a 1984 American musical comedy film directed by Frank Oz . It is the third of a series of live - action musical feature films starring Jim Henson 's Muppets with special appearances by Art Carney , James Coco , Dabney Coleman , Gregory Hines , Linda Lavin , and Joan Rivers .

The Giant Void ( also known as the Giant Void in NGH , Canes Venatici Supervoid , and AR - Lp 36 ) is an extremely large region of space of underdensity of galaxies within the constellation Canes Venatici .
Lambda Leporis ( λ Lep ) is a star in the constellation Lepus .
HD 90853 , also called s Carinae ( s Car ) , is a star in the constellation Carina .
HD 82943 ( 164 G. Hydrae ) is a yellow dwarf star approximately 89 light - years away in the constellation of Hydra .
14 Arietis ( abbreviated 14 Ari ) is a star in the constellation of Aries .
Lowery Glacier ( 82 ° 35′S 163 ° 15′E ) is a glacier about 60 nautical miles ( 110 km ) long , which flows north from Prince Andrew Plateau , Antarctica , along the east side of the Queen Elizabeth Range to enter Nimrod Glacier .
Holdsworth Glacier ( 86 ° 30′S 154 ° 0′W ) is a tributary glacier about 8 nautical miles ( 15 km ) long , flowing northeast from Fuller Dome to enter the southeast side of Bartlett Glacier , in the Queen Maud Mountains of Antarctica .
Walsham Rocks is a group of rocks lying 1 nautical mile ( 1.9 km ) east of Buff island , at the southwest end of the Palmer Archipelago , off the coast of Antarctica .
Guerrero Glacier ( 78 ° 32′S 84 ° 15′W ) is a glacier about 7 nautical miles ( 13 km ) long in Doyran Heights , draining from the southeast slopes of Mount Havener southwest of Beloslav Peak to the south side of Taylor Spur , in the southeast part of the Sentinel Range , Ellsworth Mountains , Antarctica .
Dimcha Peak ( Bulgarian : връх Димча , `` Vrah Dimcha '' \'vr&h ' dim - cha\ ) is the rocky , partly ice - free peak rising to 650 m in southeastern Poibrene Heights on Blagoevgrad Peninsula , Oscar II Coast in Graham Land , Antarctica .
Heed Rock ( 64 ° 59′S 63 ° 47′W ) is a very small rock , awash at high water and virtually hidden from sight , lying 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) south of Brown Island in the Wauwermans Islands in the Wilhelm Archipelago , Antarctica .
Emeline Island is a conspicuous rocky island rising to over 100 m ( 328 ft ) in the Aitcho group on the west side of English Strait in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Inclusion Hill ( 77 ° 15′S 166 ° 26′E ) is a prominent steeply conical hill , 335 metres ( 1,100 ft ) high , between McDonald Beach and the Mount Bird icecap on Ross Island , Antarctica .
Grazzini Bay is an ice - filled coastal embayment , 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) , between Gentile Point and Fisher Point on the east side of the Darley Hills , in the Churchill Mountains of Antarctica .
The Grove Mountains are a large , scattered group of mountains and nunataks extending over an area of approximately 40 by 20 miles ( 60 by 30 km ) , located 100 miles ( 160 km ) east of the Mawson Escarpment in American Highland , Antarctica .
Kosco Glacier ( 84 ° 27′S 178 ° 0′W ) is a glacier about 20 nautical miles ( 40 km ) long , flowing from the Anderson Heights vicinity of the Bush Mountains of Antarctica northward to enter the Ross Ice Shelf between Wilson Portal and Mount Speed .
Schloredt Nunatak ( 75 ° 3′S 134 ° 15′W ) is a nunatak 1 nautical mile ( 1.9 km ) south of Bleclic Peaks , at the south extremity of the Perry Range in Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Keller Peninsula is a high peninsula separating Mackellar Inlet and Martel Inlet in Admiralty Bay , on King George Island , in the South Shetland Islands of Antarctica .
Bond Point is a small ice - free headland on the south coast of western Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica forming the northeast side of the entrance to Kavarna Cove .
Cape Worsley ( 64 ° 39′S 60 ° 24′W ) is a dome - shaped cape 225 m high with snow - free cliffs on the south and east sides , lying 10 nautical miles ( 18 km ) east of the south end of Detroit Plateau on Nordenskjöld Coast in Graham Land , Antarctica .
The Meteorite Hills ( 79 ° 40′S 155 ° 36′E ) are a group of hills , 11 nautical miles ( 20 km ) long , forming the western portion of the Darwin Mountains in Antarctica .
Chavei Cove ( Bulgarian : залив Чавеи , `` Zaliv Chavei '' \'za - liv cha-'ve - i\ ) is the 2.2 km wide cove indenting for 900 m the southeast coast of Rozhen Peninsula on Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica entered east of Gela Point .
Hessler Peak ( 79 ° 37′S 84 ° 2′W ) is a sharp peak , 1,670 metres ( 5,480 ft ) high , at the south end of Dunbar Ridge in the Heritage Range in Antarctica .
LaForrest Rock ( 85 ° 6′S 164 ° 32′W ) is a rock outcrop 1.5 nautical miles ( 3 km ) west of the mouth of Strom Glacier , along the low , ice - covered north slopes of the Duncan Mountains , Antarctica .
Puccini Spur ( 70 ° 3′S 70 ° 38′W ) is a rock spur , 6 nautical miles ( 11 km ) long , extending southwest into the Mozart Ice Piedmont close south of Mahler Spur in the north part of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Kuber Peak ( Vrah Kuber \'vr&h ' ku - ber\ ) is a 770 m peak in Delchev Ridge , Tangra Mountains on Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Holst Point ( 65 ° 32′S 63 ° 50′W ) is a point at the head of Beascochea Bay which divides it into two arms , on the west coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Viking Heights is a prominent flat - topped mountain , 2,960 m , between Tanngarden Peaks and Mount Wideroe in the Sor Rondane Mountains , Antarctica .
Eremiya Hill ( Bulgarian : Еремийски хълм , `` Eremiyski Halm '' \e - re-'miy - ski ' h&lm\ ) is an ice - covered hill rising to 863 m in the west part of Marescot Ridge on Trinity Peninsula in Graham Land , Antarctica .
McDonald Bay is an open bay in the Davis Sea , 10 nautical miles ( 19 km ) wide at its entrance between Adams Island and the Haswell Islands , lying immediately west of Mabus Point on the coast of Antarctica .
Ferrier Peninsula is a narrow peninsula , 2.4 km ( 1.5 mi ) long , forming the eastern end of Laurie Island in the South Orkney Islands of Antarctica .
Cape Hattersley - Smith ( 71 ° 51′S 61 ° 4′W ) is a cape marked by a triangular rock peak at the southeast end of Condor Peninsula , 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) southwest of Cape Knowles , on the Black Coast of Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Rodman Cove is a cove south of Cape Lindsey on the west coast of Elephant Island , in the South Shetland Islands of Antarctica .
The Marion Nunataks are a small group of nunataks rising to about 600 m ( 2,000 ft ) on Charcot Island , in the eastern Bellinghausen Sea of Antarctica .
Moran Buttress ( 85 ° 31′S 125 ° 38′W ) is a steep bluff 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) south of Koopman Peak , rising over 2,600 metres ( 8,500 ft ) and forming a major projection between Davisville Glacier and Quonset Glacier along the north wall of the Wisconsin Range in Antarctica .
George V Land is a segment of Antarctica part of the land claimed as part of the Australian Antarctic Territory , inland from the George V Coast .
Mrahori Saddle ( Bulgarian : седловина Мрахори , `` Sedlovina Mrahori '' \se - dlo - vi-'na mra-'ho - ri\ ) is the ice - covered saddle of elevation 1350 m on Nordenskjöld Coast in Graham Land , Antarctica linking Kyustendil Ridge to the north to Lovech Heights to the south .
Kvithamaren Cliff ( 71 ° 59′S 5 ° 2′E ) is a cliff just east of Slokstallen Mountain in the Mühlig - Hofmann Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Hedley Glacier ( 77 ° 48′S 162 ° 7′E ) is a small glacier in the Kukri Hills of Victoria Land , Antarctica , flowing south from Mount Coates into Ferrar Glacier .
Inverleith Harbour is a small bay between Andrews Point and Briggs Peninsula along the northeast coast of Anvers Island , in the Palmer Archipelago , Antarctica .
The Madder Cliffs are reddish rock cliffs which form the north side of the entrance to Suspiros Bay , at the west end of Joinville Island , Antarctica .
Katedralen Canyon ( 71 ° 52′S 6 ° 33′E ) is an ice - filled canyon with steep rock cliffs indenting the northwest side of Jøkulkyrkja Mountain , in the Mühlig - Hofmann Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Knack Point ( 85 ° 15′S 118 ° 50′W ) is a point at the termination of a flat - topped spur which marks the north end of the Long Hills in the Horlick Mountains of Antarctica .
Mount Solus ( 68 ° 50′S 65 ° 33′W ) is a conspicuous , isolated mountain ( 1,290 m ) in the center and near the mouth of Weyerhaeuser Glacier , in southern Graham Land , the northernmost part of the mainland of Antarctica .

Beloslav Peak ( Bulgarian : връх Белослав , `` Vrah Beloslav '' \'vr&h be - lo-'slav\ ) is the peak rising to 2100 m in Doyran Heights , southeast Sentinel Range in Ellsworth Mountains , Antarctica , and surmounting Guerrero Glacier to the southwest and Sikera Valley to the east .
Mansergh Snowfield ( 82 ° 1′S 159 ° 50′E ) is a snowfield in Antarctica feeding the central portion of Starshot Glacier , separating the Surveyors Range and Holyoake Range .
The Kershaw Ice Rumples ( 78 ° 45′S 75 ° 40′W ) are a large area of disturbed ice between Fletcher Ice Rise and Korff Ice Rise , in the southwestern part of the Ronne Ice Shelf , Antarctica .
The Flatvaer Islands ( Norwegian : Flatvær ) , also known as the Ongul Islands are a group of small islands , of which Ongul Island is the largest , lying at the east side of the entrance of Lützow - Holm Bay , 4 km from the coastline of Antarctica .
Isluga is part of the Andean Volcanic Belt , the volcanic zone on the western side of South America where the Nazca plate is subducted beneath the South American plate .
Mount Lopatin ( 72 ° 51′S 168 ° 4′E ) is a mountain , 2,670 metres ( 8,760 ft ) high , situated 6 nautical miles ( 11 km ) east - southeast of Mount Riddolls in the Victory Mountains of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Crystal Sound ( 66 ° 23′S 66 ° 30′W ) is a sound in Antarctica between the southern part of the Biscoe Islands and the coast of Graham Land , with northern limit Cape Evensen to Cape Leblond and southern limit Holdfast Point , Roux Island , Liard Island and the Sillard Islands .
Helms Bluff ( 78 ° 29′S 164 ° 25′E ) is a prominent north - facing bluff 10 nautical miles ( 19 km ) east of Mount Morning in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Hallett Ridge ( 71 ° 15′S 176 ° 50′E ) is an undersea ridge in the Ross Sea , off the coast of Antarctica .
Mount Fridovich ( 85 ° 27′S 148 ° 12′W ) is a small mountain in Antarctica , 440 metres ( 1,440 ft ) high , standing at the north side of the terminus of Leverett Glacier and marking the western limit of the Harold Byrd Mountains .
Mount F. L. Smith ( 83 ° 38′S 169 ° 29′E ) is a mountain , 2,635 metres ( 8,650 ft ) high , standing 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) northeast of Mount Fox in the Queen Alexandra Range of Antarctica .
Gela Point ( Nos Gela \'nos ge-'la\ ) is a point on the southeast coast of Rozhen Peninsula on Livingston Island , Antarctica formed by an offshoot of Yambol Peak .
Dreyfus Point is a rounded low point on the west coast of Ioannes Paulus II Peninsula , western Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
The Fowler Islands ( 66 ° 25′S 66 ° 26′W ) are a group of small islands lying between the Bernal Islands and the Bragg Islands in Crystal Sound , off the coast of Antarctica .
Batuliya Point ( Bulgarian : нос Батулия , `` Nos Batuliya '' \'nos ba-'tu - li - ya\ ) is an ice - free tipped point forming the east extremity of Robert Island and the south side of the entrance to Tsepina Cove in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Lemanis Valley ( 80 ° 1′S 155 ° 50′E ) is a partly ice - free valley intruded at the entrance by a lobe of ice from Hatherton Glacier , lying between Ituna Valley and Lindum Valley and 7 nautical miles ( 13 km ) west - northwest of Derrick Peak in the Britannia Range , Antarctica .
Siddins Point ( 62 ° 32′41.8``S 60 ° 26′05''W ) is a point projecting into the middle of the head of Hero Bay on the north coast of Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Halfway Nunatak ( 78 ° 23′S 161 ° 6′E ) is an isolated nunatak in the Antarctica , on the west side of The Landing , and almost in the center of the upper Skelton Glacier .
Giza Peak ( 71 ° 20′S 68 ° 16′W ) is a peak rising to about 600 metres ( 2,000 ft ) on the east side of the Fossil Bluff massif , eastern Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Horizon Bluff ( 77 ° 54′S 160 ° 27′E ) is a steep bluff at the head of Beacon Valley , rising to 2,275 metres ( 7,460 ft ) to the west of Friedmann Valley in the Quartermain Mountains of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Rapa Nui Point is a rocky point projecting 180 m westwards into Shirreff Cove from the west coast of the small ( 2.6 km by 1.6 km ) ice - free promontory forming the north extremity of Ioannes Paulus II Peninsula , western Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica and ending up in Cape Shirreff .
Cape Wood ( 71 ° 24′S 169 ° 18′E ) is a point marking the east extremity of Flat Island at the western entrance to Robertson Bay , Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Haskill Nunatak ( 83 ° 24′S 51 ° 45′W ) is an elongate nunatak , 1,710 metres ( 5,610 ft ) high , standing 2.5 nautical miles ( 5 km ) west of Dyrdal Peak in the southern Forrestal Range of the Pensacola Mountains , Antarctica .
The Moss Islands are a group of small islands and rocks lying east of Midas Island and north of Apéndice Island in Hughes Bay , off the west coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Golubaya Bay ( 69 ° 58′S 9 ° 50′E ) is a bay in the southeast extremity of Kamenev Bight , along the ice shelf fringing the coast of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Festive Plateau ( 79 ° 24′S 157 ° 30′E ) is an ice - covered plateau over 2,200 metres ( 7,200 ft ) high , about 10 nautical miles ( 20 km ) long and 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) wide , just north of Mount Longhurst in the Churchill Mountains of Antarctica .
Johnstone Ridge ( 80 ° 8′S 156 ° 40′E ) is a mainly ice - free ridge in the Britannia Range , Antarctica , extending for 7 nautical miles ( 13 km ) northward from Mount Olympus toward the south side of Hatherton Glacier .
Moore Pyramid ( 70 ° 18′S 65 ° 8′E ) is a snow - covered mountain , resembling a pyramid , standing 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) northwest of Mount Wishart on the north side of Scylla Glacier in the Prince Charles Mountains of Antarctica .
Ufs Island ( 67 ° 28′S 61 ° 8′E ) is a rocky island 3.2 km ( 2 mi ) wide , lying in the east part of Howard Bay , Antarctica , just north of the Lachal Bluffs , and about 4 km ( 2.5 mi ) west of Allison Bay .
MacKinnon Glacier ( 71 ° 32′S 163 ° 13′E ) is a glacier flowing northward along the west side of Reilly Ridge into Sledgers Glacier in the Lanterman Range of the Bowers Mountains , Antarctica .
Ongley Island is a rugged rocky island lying off the north coast of Greenwich Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Mount Woollard ( 80 ° 33′S 96 ° 43′W ) is a mountain ( 2,675 m ) nearly 240 km ( 150 mi ) west of the Heritage Range , Ellsworth Mountains , in Antarctica .
Midas Island is an island lying north - west of Apéndice Island in Hughes Bay , off the west coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Zavala Island ( Bulgarian : остров Завала , `` Ostrov Zavala '' ' os - trov ' za - va - la ) is an ice - free island in the Dunbar group off the northwest coast of Varna Peninsula on Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Gobamme Rock ( 68 ° 22′S 41 ° 56′E ) is an exposed rock standing on the coast between Kozo Rock and Byōbu Rock in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Grimes Ridge ( 74 ° 38′S 110 ° 30′W ) is a high , mostly ice - covered ridge at the north side of Holt Glacier on Bear Peninsula , Walgreen Coast , in Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Mount Frazier ( 77 ° 52′S 154 ° 58′W ) is the northernmost peak of the Rockefeller Mountains , standing 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) north of Mount Jackling on Edward VII Peninsula in Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Scuttle Valley ( 76 ° 38′S 161 ° 9′E ) is a small deglaciated valley with meltwater lakes that lies parallel to and just south of Towle Glacier in the Convoy Range , Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Avalanche Rocks ( 66 ° 31′S 98 ° 2′E ) is a vertical rock outcrop rising to 185 metres ( 600 ft ) , midway between Delay Point and Jones Rocks on the west side of Melba Peninsula , Antarctica .
Gargoyle Bastion is a rocky headland rising to 60 m on the northwest coast of Varna Peninsula , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica and forming the south side of the entrance to Hydra Cove and the northeast side of the entrance to Griffin Cove .
Cotopaxi is an active stratovolcano in the Andes Mountains , located in the Latacunga canton of Cotopaxi Province , about 50 km ( 31 mi ) south of Quito , and 33 km ( 21 mi ) northeast of the city of Latacunga , Ecuador , in South America .
Varna Peninsula ( Poluostrov Varna \po - lu-'os - trov ' var - na\ ) is a roughly rectangular predominantly ice - covered peninsula forming the northeast extremity of Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Azerbaijan ( i/ˌæzərbaɪˈdʒɑːn/ AZ - ər - by - JAHN ; Azerbaijani : Azərbaycan ( ɑzærbɑjdʒɑn ) ) , officially the Republic of Azerbaijan ( Azerbaijani : Azərbaycan Respublikası ) , is a transcontinental country in the Caucasus region , situated at the crossroads of Eastern Europe and Western Asia .

Lake Miers ( 78 ° 6′S 163 ° 51′E ) is a small lake in Miers Valley , Antarctica , lying 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) east of the snouts of Miers Glacier and Adams Glacier , and filled by meltwater from these glaciers .
Klevekåpa Mountain ( 72 ° 2′S 7 ° 37′E ) is an icecapped mountain , 2,910 metres ( 9,550 ft ) high , with an abrupt southeast rock face , standing close northwest of the mouth of Snuggerud Glacier in the Filchner Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Edith Ronne Land is the portion of Antarctica bounded by Palmer Land and Ellsworth Land to the west , Queen Elizabeth Land to the south , and Coats Land to the east .
Andrews Peak ( 72 ° 17′S 165 ° 25′E ) is an Antarctic peak , 2,400 metres ( 7,900 ft ) high , in the Destination Nunataks , 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) west of Pyramid Peak in northern Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Fleece Glacier ( 65 ° 54′S 63 ° 10′W ) is a tributary glacier that enters Leppard Glacier on its north side about 1.5 nautical miles ( 3 km ) east of Moider Peak , on the east side of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Albrecht Penck Glacier ( 76 ° 40′S 162 ° 20′E ) is a glacier between the Fry Glacier and the Evans Piedmont Glacier , draining northeast toward Tripp Bay on the coast of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Bradley Ridge ( 70 ° 14′S 65 ° 15′E ) is a rock ridge in Antarctica , about 7 nautical miles ( 13 km ) southeast of Mount Peter in the Athos Range , Prince Charles Mountains .
Kinsey Ridge is a flat - topped , partly ice - covered ridge in the middle of Strauss Glacier , near the coast of Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Lieske Glacier ( 80 ° 5′S 156 ° 50′E ) is a tributary glacier draining the north slopes of Mount Olympus in the Britannia Range , Antarctica , and flowing north between Johnstone Ridge and Dusky Ridge into Hatherton Glacier .
Mount Steere is a prominent shield volcano standing 6.4 km ( 4 mi ) NNW of Mount Frakes in the Crary Mountains of Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Paradise Harbor , also known as Paradise Bay , is a wide embayment behind Lemaire and Bryde Islands in Antarctica , indenting the west coast of Graham Land between Duthiers and Leniz Points .
Maury Bay ( 66 ° 33′S 124 ° 42′E ) is an ice - filled bay indenting the coast of Antarctica just east of Cape Lewis .

Mozart Ice Piedmont ( 70 ° 0′S 71 ° 0′W ) is an ice piedmont , 60 nautical miles ( 110 km ) long - running in a NW - SE direction and 15 nautical miles ( 28 km ) wide in its widest part , on the west coast of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
The Lichen Hills ( 73 ° 18′S 162 ° 0′E ) are an escarpment - like range of hills located 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) south of the Caudal Hills on the west margin of upper Rennick Glacier , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .

For Gordon Bunshaft is a 2006 sculpture by Dan Graham , installed at the Hirshhorn Museum and Sculpture Garden in Washington , D.C. The work , which refers to American architect Gordon Bunshaft , was installed by the reflection pool of the Sunken Sculpture Garden on May 30 , 2008 .
Big John , Little John was an American Saturday - morning situation comedy , produced by Sherwood Schwartz , which starred Herbert Edelman as `` Big John '' and Robert `` Robbie '' Rist as `` Little John . ''
Spring Frost is an 1919 painting by the Australian artist Elioth Gruner .
Written by Russell T Davies , it tells the story of teenager Tess Hunter and her mother , who move to the seemingly idyllic rural village of Century Falls , only to find that it hides many powerful secrets .
Blue Horses or Die grossen blauen Pferde ( The Large Blue Horses ) is a 1911 painting by German painter and printmaker Franz Marc ( 1880 - -1916 ) .
Sponsa de Libano ( The Bride of Lebanon ) is a painting by the Pre - Raphaelite artist Edward Burne - Jones dated 1891 .
Old Church Tower at Nuenen ( or The Peasants ' Churchyard ) are names given to several oil paintings and drawings created in 1884 and 1885 by Vincent van Gogh .
Mademoiselle Rose ( also Seated Nude ) is a painting by French Romantic artist Eugène Delacroix , regarded as the leader of the French Romantic school .
Freaks and Geeks is an American teen comedy - drama television series , created by Paul Feig with Judd Apatow as executive producer , that aired on NBC during the 1999 - -2000 television season .
John J. Pershing General of the Armies , is a public artwork by American artist Robert White , located at Pershing Park in Washington , D.C. , United States .

The one - hour drama is based on the Rizzoli & Isles series of novels by Tess Gerritsen .
Gwenfritz is a painted steel abstract stabile , by Alexander Calder .
The Gay Liberation Monument is a monument featuring the sculpture Gay Liberation by American artist George Segal , located in Christopher Park along Christopher Street in Manhattan , New York .
The Dick Tracy Show is an American animated television series based on Chester Gould 's comic strip crime fighter .
Courage the Cowardly Dog is an American animated comedy horror television series created by John R. Dilworth for Cartoon Network as part of the network 's Cartoon Cartoons block .
The Waldseemüller map , Universalis Cosmographia , is a printed wall map of the world by German cartographer Martin Waldseemüller , originally published in April 1507 .
His Highness the Prince is an object - sculpture made by Joan Miró in 1974 and now part of the permanent collection of the Joan Miró Foundation in Barcelona .
The Dresden Triptych ( or Virgin and Child with St. Michael and St. Catherine and a Donor , or Triptych of the Virgin and Child ) is a very small hinged - triptych altarpiece by the Early Netherlandish painter Jan van Eyck .
Dirty Jobs is a TV series on the Discovery Channel in which host Mike Rowe is shown performing difficult , strange , disgusting , or messy occupational duties alongside the typical employees .
The Four Philosophers is a 1611 - 12 painting by Peter Paul Rubens .
Child with Toy Hand Grenade in Central Park , New York City , USA ( 1962 ) is a famous photograph by Diane Arbus .

Religion saved by Spain is an oil on canvas painting produced between 1572 - 1575 by the Italian master of the Venetian school , Titian ( c. 1488/(1482 ) -- 1576 ) commemorating the Battle of Lepanto .
La belle ferronnière is a portrait of a woman , usually attributed to Leonardo da Vinci , in the Louvre .
The Three Smiths Statue is a sculpture by Felix Nylund , situated in Helsinki in Three Smiths Square at the intersection of Aleksanterinkatu and Mannerheimintie .
Grlom u jagode ( `` The Unpicked Strawberries '' ) is a 1975 Yugoslavian TV series directed by Srđan Karanović and co - written by Karanović and Rajko Grlić .
UIC Skyspace is a skyspace by James Turrell located at the southwest corner of Roosevelt Road and Halsted Street in Chicago .
Top of the Lake is a mystery drama television series written by Jane Campion and Gerard Lee , and directed by Campion and Garth Davis .
The Ildefonso Altarpiece is a triptych painting by Peter Paul Rubens , dating to between 1630 and 1631 .
The Four Witches ( German : Die Vier Hexen , or Four Naked Women or Four Sorceresses ) is a 1497 engraving by the German Renaissance master Albrecht Dürer .
In Finnish mythology , the Sampo or Sammas was a magical artifact of indeterminate type constructed by Ilmarinen that brought good fortune to its holder .
Portrait of a Kleptomaniac or Portrait of an Insane Person ( French : L'Aliéné or Le Kleptomane ) is an 1822 oil painting by Théodore Géricault .
Still Life and Street is a woodcut print by the Dutch artist M. C. Escher which was first printed in March , 1937 .
The Old Fox ( original German title `` Der Alte '' , lit . `` The Old Man '' ) is a German crime drama created by Helmut Ringelmann .
The Watts Towers , Towers of Simon Rodia , or Nuestro Pueblo ( `` our town '' ) are a collection of 17 interconnected sculptural structures within the Simon Rodia State Historic Park in the Watts community of Los Angeles .

Biggs ( John Burville Biggs ) , born in Hobart , Tasmania in 1934 , is an Australian educational psychologist and novelist who developed the SOLO Taxonomy for assessing the quality of learning outcomes , and the model of constructive alignment for designing teaching and assessment ( Biggs , 2007 ) .

Streets of Rage 3 , known in Japan as Bare Knuckle III ( ベア・ナックルIII ) and subtitled Tekken Seiten ( 鉄拳聖典 lit . Iron Fist Scriptures ) in pre - release media and the official soundtrack release , is a side - scrolling beat 'em up released by Sega in 1994 for the Sega Mega Drive / Genesis .

Super Doubles Tennis is an arcade game released by Data East in 1983 .

Armored Fist 3 is a tank simulation video game developed and published by NovaLogic , released on October 12 , 1999 .
Game Dev Tycoon was created by Greenheart Games , a company founded in July 2012 by brothers Patrick and Daniel Klug .
Banjo - Kazooie is a platform video game developed by Rare and originally released for the Nintendo 64 video game console on 29 June 1998 in North America and 17 July 1998 in Europe .
Spy Fiction ( スパイフィクション ) is a 2003 stealth - based video game by Access Games for the PlayStation 2 .
Heroes of Might and Magic IV is a turn - based strategy game developed by Gus Smedstad through New World Computing and published by the 3DO Company for Microsoft Windows - based personal computers in 2002 .
Worms Ultimate Mayhem is an artillery strategy game developed by Team17 .
Max Payne is a third - person shooter action thriller video game developed by Remedy Entertainment and published by Gathering of Developers in July 2001 for Microsoft Windows .
Scooter Shooter is a horizontal - scrolling shooter arcade game developed by Konami in 1985 with competitive play against either a computer opponent or another player .
Frogs and Flies is a 1982 video game by Mattel for the Atari 2600 and Commodore 64 platforms .
Synergy was added to the IBM 's Rational Software family of SCM tools and named Rational Synergy .
WorldShift is a science fiction tactical role - playing game video game released in 2008 by Crytek Black Sea .
ArcEditor is the midlevel software suite designed for advanced editing of spatial data published in the proprietary Esri format .

Ball Fighter is a puzzle video game developed by Teyon for the Nintendo DSiWare .
Mystic Heroes , released in Japan as Battle Houshin ( バトル封神 ) , is a beat 'em up video game developed by Koei .
Boom Blox Bash Party is a physics - based puzzle video game developed by EA Los Angeles and Amblin Entertainment and published by Electronic Arts for the Wii video game console .
Ms. Splosion Man is a platform video game developed by Twisted Pixel Games , and was released on Xbox 360 on July 13 , 2011 as well as Windows Phone .
Tony Hawk 's Underground 2 is the sixth installment in Neversoft 's Tony Hawk 's series and is the sequel to Tony Hawk 's Underground .
Guilty Gear X2 , also known as Guilty Gear XX ( Japanese : ギルティギア イグゼクス Hepburn : Giruti Gia Iguzekusu ) and subtitled The Midnight Carnival in Japan , is a fighting game developed by Arc System Works and published by Sammy Studios .
Galaxian 3 ( also known as Galaxian³ : Project Dragoon ) is an arcade game released by Namco in 1990 and its immediate sequel as a scaled - down arcade cabinet in 1994 .

Beyond Divinity is a role - playing video game from Larian Studios , which followed up on Divine Divinity and was published on April 28 , 2004 .
Project Stealth Fighter is a combat flight simulator released in 1987 by MicroProse , featuring a fictional United States military aircraft .
Mean 18 is the name of a series of computer golf games released by Accolade in the late 1980s and early 1990s .
Starsiege is a mecha - style vehicle simulation game developed by Dynamix and released in 1999 .
Actua Pool is a sports simulation video game developed by British company Gremlin Interactive as part of their highly successful Actua Sports series of sport simulators of the mid - to - late 1990s .
Escape from Monkey Island is a computer adventure game developed and released by LucasArts in 2000 .
Tropico 5 is a semi - democratic construction and management simulation video game developed by Haemimont Games and released on 23 May 2014 .
Rack ' Em Up is a Billiards / Pool arcade game developed by Konami in 1987 with two game types : 9-Ball or Rotation .
GP-1 is a motorcycle racing game developed by Genki and published by Atlus for the SNES , which was released in 1993 .
Windows Home Server 2011 , code named Vail , is a home server operating system by Microsoft designed for small office / home offices and homes with multiple connected PCs to offer protected file storage , file sharing , automated PC backup , remote access , and remote control of PC desktops .
Kinect Sports is a sports video game developed by Rare and published by Microsoft Game Studios for the Xbox 360 .
World Series Baseball ' 95 is a traditional baseball simulation video game by Sega that allows players to put teams involved in the 1994 Major League Baseball season in either exhibition , regular season , or playoff mode .
Battle.net is an internet - based online gaming , digital distribution , and digital rights management platform developed by Blizzard Entertainment .
Sid Meier 's Covert Action is an action and strategy video game developed and released in 1990 by MicroProse for the DOS and the Amiga .
Faith Fighter is an online fighting game developed by the Italian website Molleindustria in which players fight as religious figures such as Buddha , Jesus or Muhammad and must fight Xenu after beating all playable characters .
Burnout Dominator is a racing game developed and published by Electronic Arts for the PlayStation 2 and PlayStation Portable .

Golden Axe II is a side - scrolling beat 'em up video game developed and published by Sega , first released on the Sega Genesis in December 1991 .

Anna Cecilia Malmström ( born 15 May 1968 ) is a Swedish politician who has served as European Commissioner for Trade since 2014 , having previously served as European Commissioner for Home Affairs from 2010 to 2014 .

Charles Renard ( 1847 - -1905 ) born in Damblain , Vosges , was a French military engineer .

Antoine Magnan ( 13 June 1881 -- 5 March 1938 ) was a French zoologist and aeronautical engineer who studied the flight of insects and birds for possible lessons to apply to powered flight .

Diego Arias de Miranda ( December 1 , 1845 , Aranda de Duero -- June 28 , 1929 ) was a Spanish politician linked to Christian naturalism .

Cabret was a Spanish translator active towards the end of the fourteenth century .

David Kynaston ( /ˈkɪnəstən/ ; born 30 July 1951 in Aldershot ) is an English historian specializing in the social history of England .

Jean Louis de Nogaret de La Valette ( 1554 - -1642 ) , created Duke of Épernon , was a powerful member of the French nobility at the turn of the 16th century .
Charles Wesley ( /ˈwɛsli , ˈwɛzli/ ; 18 December 1707 -- 29 March 1788 ) was an English leader of the Methodist movement , most widely known for writing more than 6,000 hymns .
Magnus Hirschfeld ( 14 May 1868 -- 14 May 1935 ) was a Jewish German physician and sexologist educated primarily in Germany ; he based his practice in Berlin - Charlottenburg .
Elia Levita ( 13 February 1469 -- 28 January 1549 ) , ( Hebrew : אליהו בן אשר הלוי אשכנזי ) also known as Elijah Levita , Elias Levita , Élie Lévita , Elia Levita Ashkenazi , Eliahu Bakhur ( `` Eliahu the Bachelor '' ) was a Renaissance Hebrew grammarian , scholar and poet .
Henning Graf Reventlow , full name Henning Lothar Gert Count Reventlow ( September 22 , 1929 - September 9 , 2010 ) was a German Protestant theologian , Old Testament scholar and university professor .
Étienne Louis Geoffroy ( October 12 , 1725 -- August 12 , 1810 ) was a French entomologist and pharmacist .
Sir Edwin Arnold KCIE CSI ( 10 June 1832 -- 24 March 1904 ) was an English poet and journalist , who is most known for his work , The Light of Asia .
Giampiero Galeazzi ( born 18 May 1946 ) is an Italian former competition rower , sport journalist , commentator and television personality .
Alberto Undiano Mallenco ( born 8 October 1973 in Pamplona ) is a Spanish football referee who currently resides in Ansoáin .
Otto Benndorf ( September 13 , 1838 -- January 2 , 1907 ) was a German - Austrian archaeologist who was a native of Greiz .
Zuber Usman ( 12 December 1916 -- 25 July 1976 ) was an Indonesian teacher and writer , known as an early pioneer of Indonesian literary criticism .
Luis María Larrañaga Merlo ( born June 13 , 1966 ) , known as Luis Merlo , is a Spanish actor .
Nathalie Luca ( born 1966 ) is a French research director at the French National Centre for Scientific Research ( CNRS ) , an anthropologist and a sociologist of religions .

Andrés Marcos Burriel y López ( 1719 - -1762 ) was a Spanish Jesuit historian , essayist , notable for editing Miguel Venegas ' Empresas Apostólicas and publishing it using Venegas ' name as Noticia de la California in 1757 .
Ante Ciliga ( 20 February 1898 - 21 October 1992 ) was a Croatian politician , writer and publisher .
Gudrun Ensslin ( German : ( ˈɡuːdʁuːn ˈɛnsliːn ) ; 15 August 1940 -- 18 October 1977 ) was a founder of the German urban guerilla group Red Army Faction ( Rote Armee Fraktion , or RAF , also known as the Baader - Meinhof Gang ) .
Philippe Cuper is a French clarinetist , born in Lille on April 25 , 1957 .

Abel Matutes y Juan ( born 31 October 1941 ) is a Spanish politician who served as Spain 's Minister of Foreign Affairs from 6 May 1996 to 2000 .
Hermann Schroeder ( 26 March 1904 -- 7 October 1984 ) was a German composer and a Catholic church musician .
Stephen Kelman is an English novelist , whose debut novel Pigeon English was a shortlisted nominee for the 2011 Man Booker Prize .

Navya Natarajan is an Indian film actress mainly acted in Malayalam , Kannada and Telugu films .

Daniel Domscheit - Berg ( né Berg ; born 1978 ) , previously known under the pseudonym Daniel Schmitt , is a German technology activist .

Naum Veqilharxhi born Naum Bredhi ( 1797 - 1854 ) was an Albanian lawyer and scholar .
David Ferdinand Koreff ( 1 February 1783 -- 15 May 1851 ) was a German physician who was a personal doctor of Staatskanzler Karl August von Hardenberg and occupied one of the two chairs for animal magnetism created in 1817 at the University of Berlin .
Adalberto Libera ( Italian pronunciation : ( adal'bɛrto ˈliːbera ) ; 16 July 1903 - 17 March 1963 ) is one of the most representative architects of the Italian Modern movement .

Peter Przygodda ( 26 October 1941 -- 2 October 2011 ) was a German filmmaker , best known for editing Wim Wenders ' films .
Pertev Naili Boratav , born Mustafa Pertev ( September 2 , 1907 -- March 16 , 1998 ) was a Turkish folklorist and researcher of folk literature .

Ponç de la Guàrdia ( or Pons de la Guardia ; fl . 1154 - -1188 ) was a Catalan knight of the family of Saguàrdia , lords of the castle of Ripoll .

Jelleke Veenendaal ( born 15 December 1953 in Alkmaar ) is a Dutch politician and member of House of Representatives for the People 's Party for Freedom and Democracy ( VVD ) .

John Reid , Baron Reid of Cardowan ( born 8 May 1947 ) is a British Labour Party politician .
Nazario Herrera Ortega ( born 28 July 1964 ) is a Mexican politician from the Institutional Revolutionary Party ( formerly from the National Action Party . From 2010 to 2012 he served as Deputy of the LXI Legislature of the Mexican Congress representing Tlaxcala .
Lorenz Caffier ( 24 December 1954 in Weixdorf , Saxony ) is the chairman of the Christian Democratic Union in the German state of Mecklenburg - Western Pomerania .
David Lott is a British former politician , best known as a political organiser for the UK Independence Party ( UKIP ) .
Dawn Primarolo , Baroness Primarolo , DBE PC ( born 2 May 1954 ) , is a British Labour Party politician who was the Member of Parliament for Bristol South from 1987 until 2015 , when she stood down .

Stanisław Jałowiecki ( born on 26 December 1946 in Tanvald ) is a Polish politician and Member of the European Parliament for the Lower Silesian Voivodship & Opole Voivodship with the Civic Platform , part of the European People 's Party and sits on the European Parliament 's Committee on Transport and Tourism .

Johnnie David Hutchins ( August 4 , 1922 -- September 4 , 1943 ) was a United States Navy sailor and a recipient of the United States military 's highest decoration -- the Medal of Honor -- for his actions in World War II . He enlisted in the Navy from Houston in November 1942 .
John R. Ryan ( born August 15 , 1945 ) is a retired United States Navy vice admiral who served as the Superintendent of the United States Naval Academy and as the Chancellor of the State University of New York .
James Trevenen ( 1 January 1760 -- 9 August 1790 ) was an officer in the Royal Navy and the Imperial Russian Navy .
Kevin B. Kuklok retired from the United States Marine Corps as a Major General after over thirty years of service .
Frank Jack Fletcher ( April 29 , 1885 -- April 25 , 1973 ) was an admiral in the United States Navy during World War II . Fletcher was the operational commander at the pivotal Battles of Coral Sea and of Midway .
The 58th ( 2/1st London ) Division was an infantry division created in 1915 as part of the massive expansion of the British Army during World War I. It was a 2nd Line Territorial Force formation raised as a duplicate of the 56th ( 1/1st London ) Division .
The Welsh Guards ( WG ) , ( Welsh : Gwarchodlu Cymreig ) , part of the Guards Division , is one of the Foot Guards regiments of the British Army .
Henry Carlton Cumberbatch ( 8 December 1900 -- 27 January 1966 ) was an officer of the British Royal Navy who served as a submarine commander before and at the start of World War II .
George Augustus Eliott , 1st Baron Heathfield , PC , KB ( 25 December 1717 -- 6 July 1790 ) was a British Army officer who served in three major wars during the eighteenth century .
Charles Mitchell Thomas ( October 1 , 1846 - -July 3 , 1908 ) was a rear admiral in the United States Navy who served for 47 years .
Walter Schindler ( December 10 , 1897 -- April 3 , 1991 ) was a highly decorated career officer in the United States Navy , who ultimately achieved the rank of Vice Admiral .
Franz Anton Itrich ( November 26 , 1853 -- June 11 , 1933 ) was a chief carpenter 's mate serving in the United States Navy during the Spanish--
Carl Ferdinand Pfeifer ( December 18 , 1915 -- May 12 , 2001 ) was an officer in the United States Navy and aid to Presidents Harry S. Truman and Dwight D. Eisenhower .
Vice Admiral William Douglas Crowder retired from the United States Navy in November 2009 after serving as the Deputy Chief of Naval Operations for Operations , Plans and Strategy ( N3/N5 ) .
Generalleutnant Kurt - Bertram von Döring ( 18 February 1889 in Ribbekardt -- 9 July 1960 in Medingen ) was a German World War II Luftwaffe Generalleutnant .
Major General ( Thomas ) Herbert Shoubridge CB , CMG , DSO ( 1871 -- 1923 ) was a British Army officer who became Commandant of the Royal Military College Sandhurst .
Colonel Harry Noel Havelock Wild OBE ( usually referred to as Noel Wild ) was a British Army officer during the Second World War .
Barrington Dacres ( died 25 October 1806 ) was an officer of the Royal Navy , who saw service during the French Revolutionary and Napoleonic Wars .
Commodore John R. Goldsborough ( 2 July 1809 -- 22 June 1877 ) was an officer in the United States Navy .
The Royal Corps of Signals ( often simply known as the Royal Signals - abbreviated to R SIGNALS ) is one of the combat support arms of the British Army .
Marshall MacDermott ( c.1791 -- 3 November 1877 ) was a British Army officer and member of the South Australian Legislative Council 1855 to 1857 and a member for the South Australian House of Assembly seat of Flinders from 1857 to 1859 .
The King 's Own Malta Regiment was a territorial infantry regiment on the British Army colonial list prior to Malta 's independence .
Thomas Cranley Onslow ( 7 October 1778 -- 7 July 1861 ) was a British politician and British Army officer , the second son of Thomas Onslow , 2nd Earl of Onslow .
The Devon and Cornwall County Division was a County Division of the British Army formed on 28 February 1941 .
Admiral Sir Alan Geoffrey Hotham KCMG CB ( 3 October 1876 -- 10 July 1965 ) was an officer in the Royal Navy .
Air Marshal Sir John Humphrey Edwardes - Jones KCB , CBE , DFC , AFC ( 15 August 1905 -- 19 January 1987 ) was a senior Royal Air Force commander .
The Wessex Regiment was a Territorial Army ( TA ) infantry regiment of the British Army between 1971 and 1995 .
Victor G. Guillory is a retired United States Navy rear admiral who , in his last position , served as the Commander , United States Fourth Fleet .
Brigadier General Carmelita Vigil - Schimmenti ( born December 16 , 1936 ) was an officer of the United States Air Force , who in 1985 became the first Hispanic female to attain the rank of Brigadier General .
Richard Nigel Cullen , DFC ( 5 June 1917 -- 4 March 1941 ) was an Australian fighter ace of World War II . Serving with the Royal Air Force ( RAF ) , he was credited with as many as sixteen aerial victories before being killed in action during the Battle of Greece .
Baldomero López ( August 23 , 1925 -- September 15 , 1950 ) was a first lieutenant in the United States Marine Corps during the Korean War .
Captain Edward Rotheram CB RN ( 27 December 1753 -- 6 November 1830 ) was a senior officer of the British Royal Navy , who served for many years during the American War of Independence , French Revolutionary War and Napoleonic Wars .
Captain William Cornwallis Symonds ( 1810 -- 23 November 1841 ) was a British Army officer who was prominent in the early colonisation of New Zealand .
Lieutenant General Erhard Bühler ( born 20 January 1956 ) is an officer of the German Army , and the current Director General for Planning German Ministry of Defence in Berlin , Germany .
The 602 Commando Company ( Spanish : Compañía de Comandos 602 ) is a special operations unit of the Argentine Army .
Admiral James Fife , Jr. ( January 22 , 1897 - November 1 , 1975 ) was a United States Navy admiral who was promoted to four star rank after retirement as a `` tombstone admiral '' .
Admiral Sir Henry D'Esterre Darby , KCB , ( 1750 - -1823 ) was an officer in the Royal Navy .
Owen Lewis Cope Williams ( 13 July 1836 -- 15 January 1913 ) was a British Army officer and Conservative politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1880 to 1885 .

The Abitibi River is a river in northeastern Ontario , Canada , which flows northwest from Lake Abitibi to join the Moose River which empties into James Bay .

The Bou Regreg ( Arabic : أبو رقراق‎ ) is a river located in western Morocco which discharges to the Atlantic Ocean between the cities of Rabat and Salé .

Norman Bethune Square ( French : Place Norman - Bethune ) is a small urban square located in Downtown Montreal at the northwest intersection of Guy Street and De Maisonneuve Boulevard West .
The Teutoburg Forest / Egge Hills Nature Park ( German : Naturpark Teutoburger Wald / Eggegebirge ) is a nature park founded in 1965 in the northeast of the German state of North Rhine - Westphalia .

Gee 's golden langur ( Trachypithecus geei ) , or simply the golden langur , is an Old World monkey found in a small region of western Assam , India and in the neighboring foothills of the Black Mountains of Bhutan .

Haloquadratum ( `` salt square '' ) is a genus of the family Halobacteriaceae .
The Chinese wren - babbler or Chinese cupwing ( Pnoepyga mutica ) is a species of bird in its own family , Pnoepygidae .
The Kura loach ( Oxynoemacheilus brandtii ) is an Asian species of freshwater fish , occurring in Armenia , Azerbaijan , Turkey and Iran .
Pterotragus lugens is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pterotragus .
Patiria , is a genus of starfish in the family Asterinidae from the Pacific Ocean .
The Jamaican laughing frog or Savanna - la - Mar tree frog , Osteopilus brunneus , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Jamaica . It is found mainly inland , and lives and lays eggs in the water contained within bromeliad leaves .
The Halidae are a tiny spider family with only three described species in two genera .
Dinokanaga is a small genus of scorpionfly belonging to the extinct family Dinopanorpidae .
Styphlodromus bicolor is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Styphlodromus .
Hoploparia is a genus of fossil lobster belonging to the family Nephropidae .
The Medeoloideae ( syn . Medeoleae ) are a subfamily of monocotyledon perennial , herbaceous mainly bulbous flowering plants in the Liliaceae ( Lily ) family .
Stuhlmann 's starling ( Poeoptera stuhlmanni ) is a species of starling in the family Sturnidae .
The taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 places Omphalotrochidae in the superfamilia Euomphaloidea within the Paleozoic molluscs with anisostrophically coiled shells of uncertain position ( Gastropoda ? ) .
The Cainarachi poison frog ( Ameerega cainarachi ; formerly Epipedobates cainarachi ) is a species of frog in the Dendrobatidae family endemic to Peru .
Furcifer antimena , also known as the Antimena chameleon , is a species of chameleon that is endemic to southwest Madagascar .
Echinoplectanum is a genus of Monopisthocotylean Monogeneans , belonging in the family Diplectanidae .
Jackson 's soft - furred mouse or Jackson 's praomys ( Praomys jacksoni ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The Petrale sole , Eopsetta jordani , is an edible flatfish of the family Pleuronectidae .
The Colares stingray , Dasyatis colarensis , is a species of stingray in the family Dasyatidae , native to the shallow brackish waters of the Amazon River estuary in northern Brazil .
The Georgian shemaya ( Alburnus derjugini ) is a species of cyprinid fish in the genus Alburnus .
Isorineloricaria spinosissima , also known as the Zucchini catfish , is a species of Loricariidae endemic to western Ecuador .
Kukufeldia is within Iguanodontia a member of the Styracosterna .
The Chinese bamboo partridge ( Bambusicola thoracicus ) is a small Galliform bird .
Antillogorgia is a genus of soft coral , sea fans in the family Gorgoniidae .
The Caracas brush finch ( Arremon phaeopleurus ) is a species of bird in the Emberizidae family .
The Sumatran spiny rat ( Maxomys hylomyoides ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .

The Surucua trogon ( Trogon surrucura ) is a species of bird in the Trogonidae family .
The Phycitinae are a subfamily of snout moths ( family Pyralidae ) .
Monodilepas is a species of small sea snail , a keyhole limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets and slit limpets .

Saniella is a flowering plant genus in the family Hypoxidaceae , native to South Africa and Lesotho .
The Anambra waxbill ( Estrilda poliopareia ) is a species of estrildid finch found in wetter land of southern Nigeria .
The Himantariidae are a family of centipedes in the order Geophilomorpha , found almost exclusively in the Northern Hemisphere .
The Magellanic woodpecker ( Campephilus magellanicus ) is a very large woodpecker found along the Andes of Chile and southwestern Argentina ; it is resident within its range .
The South American snapping turtle ( Chelydra acutirostris ) is a species of turtle in the family Chelydridae .
Grylloidea is a superfamily of insects in the order Orthoptera .
Vitrinidae is a family of small , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Limacoidea ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Chthomaloporus is an extinct genus of Anteosaurian synapsid .
Diaea is a spider genus of the family Thomisidae ( crab spiders ) .
The Skyros wall lizard ( Podarcis gaigeae ) is a species of lizard in the family Lacertidae .
Racemobambos is a genus of bamboo ( tribe Bambuseae within the Poaceae ) and the sole genus of its subtribe , the Racemobambodinae .
Cixiinae is a planthopper subfamily in the family Cixiidae .

' Keyserlingitinae is a subfamily of the Sibiritidae , Early Triassic Ammonoidea .
Callionymus simplicicornis , the Simple - spined dragonet , is a species of dragonet native to the tropical Pacific Ocean where it is known at depths of around 40 metres ( 130 ft ) .
The genus is part of the ancient Araucariaceae family of conifers , a group once widespread during the Jurassic period , but now largely restricted to the Southern Hemisphere except for a number of extant Malesian Agathis .
Hymenopodinae is a subfamily of the mantis family Hymenopodidae .
Philipomyia is a genus of ' horse fly ' belonging to the family Tabanidae subfamily Tabaninae .
The Myxosporea are a class of microscopic parasites , belonging to the Myxozoa .
Eranthis ( winter aconite ) is a genus of eight species of flowering plants in the family Ranunculaceae ( Buttercup family ) , native to southern Europe and east across Asia to Japan .
Aschisma is a genus of moss in family Pottiaceae .
The North Island snipe ( Coenocorypha barrierensis ) , also known as the little barrier snipe or tutukiwi , is an extinct species of bird in the sandpiper family , Scolopacidae , that was endemic to New Zealand .

Loxorhynchus is a genus of crabs of the eastern Pacific Ocean in the family Epialtidae .
Chondrorrhina is a genus of fruit and flower chafers belonging to the family Scarabaeidae , subfamily Cetoniinae .
Paraphysornis is an extinct genus of giant flightless predatory birds of the family Phorusrhacidae or `` terror birds '' within the subfamily Brontornithinae that lived in Brazil .
Crepidium ophrydis ( syn . of Dienia ophrydis ) is a member of the family Orchidaceae , endemic to the Philippines .
The Nihoa conehead katydid ( Banza nihoa ) is a species of katydid which is endemic to the Hawaiian island of Nihoa ( Northwestern Hawaiian Islands ) .

The Himalayan quail ( Ophrysia superciliosa ) or mountain quail is a medium - sized quail belonging to the pheasant family .

Pseudorhicnoessa is a genus of beach flies in the family Canacidae ( formally Tethinidae ) .
The Eurasian reed warbler , or just reed warbler ( Acrocephalus scirpaceus ) is an Old World warbler in the genus Acrocephalus .
The Saint Helena plover ( Charadrius sanctaehelenae ) , locally known as the wirebird due to its thin legs , is a small wader endemic to the island of Saint Helena in the mid - Atlantic .
Pseudanthus is a genus of plants under the family Picrodendraceae .
Isotomiella is a genus of springtails ( Collembola ) in the family Isotomidae .
Eobaataridae is a family of fossil mammal within the order Multituberculata .
Pandoraea is a genus of Gram - negative , nonspore - forming , motile bacteria with a single polar flagellum , of the family Burkholderiaceae and class Betaproteobacteria .
Acronema is a genus of 25 species of plants in the Apiaceae family found in the Sino - Himalayan region .
Coeliadinae is a subfamily of the skipper butterfly family ( Hesperiidae ) .
The China rockfish ( Sebastes nebulosus ) is a rockfish of the Pacific coast found from Kachemak Bay in the northern Gulf of Alaska to Redondo Beach and San Nicolas Island in southern California .
The Cocos cuckoo ( Coccyzus ferrugineus ) is a species of cuckoo in the Cuculidae family .
Megapedetes is a genus of fossil rodents related to the springhare and other species of the genus Pedetes , with which it forms the family Pedetidae .
Infectious hematopoietic necrosis virus ( IHNV ) , is a negative - sense single - stranded , bullet - shaped RNA virus that is a member of the Rhabdoviridae family , and from the genus Novirhabdovirus .
The Halmahera blossom bat ( Syconycteris carolinae ) is a species of megabat in the family Pteropodidae .
Pristis is a genus of sawfish of the family Pristidae .
S. feisti is no longer considered to be a species of Saniwa , but a more primitive member of the family Varanidae .
The Swannanoa darter ( Etheostoma swannanoa ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the perch family .
Crocker 's sea snake ( Laticauda crockeri ) is a species of venomous snake in the subfamily Hydrophiinae .
Amaryllidoideae ( Amaryllidaceae s.s . , amaryllids ) is a subfamily of monocot flowering plants in the family Amaryllidaceae , order Asparagales .
The New Zealand bittern ( Ixobrychus novaezelandiae ) is an extinct and enigmatic species of heron in the family Ardeidae .
Byrrhidae , the pill beetles , is a family of beetles in the superfamily Byrrhoidea .
The Zenker 's honeyguide ( Melignomon zenkeri ) is a species of bird in the Indicatoridae family .
Anictis is an extinct species of carnivorous cat - like mammal belonging to the superfamily Aeluroidea , endemic to Europe living from the Oligocene 33.9 - -28.4 Ma , existing for approximately 5.4 million years .
Spotted thicklip loach ( Triplophysa strauchii ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Triplophysa .
The Kuala Lumpur caecilian , Caudacaecilia nigroflava , is a species of amphibian in the Ichthyophiidae family endemic to Malaysia .
Laccosternus grouvellei is a species of beetle in the family Dytiscidae , the only species in the genus Laccosternus .
Porcellionidae is a terrestrial family of the order Isopoda .
Calliphara is a genus of insect in the family Scutelleridae ( Hemiptera ) .
Berriasella is a discoidal evolute perisphinctacean ammonite , and type genus for the neocomitid subfamily Berriasellinae .
The Jabily or `` elephant tree '' ( Operculicarya decaryi ) is a thick stemmed succulent plant species in the family Anacardiaceae , named after the botanical collector Raymond Decary .
Susannah Maidment in 2008 even listed Chialingosaurus kuani among the invalid stegosaur taxa in her phylogeny of Stegosauria .
Dichondra is a small genus of flowering plants in the morning glory family , Convolvulaceae .
The Luzon flameback ( Chrysocolaptes haematribon ) is a species of bird in the Picidae family .
Père David 's vole ( Eothenomys melanogaster ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Along with the subfamily Urocordylinae , Sauropleurinae is part of the family Urocordylidae .
The Kanadi kingfish ( Scomberomorus plurilineatus ) is a species of ray - finned bony fish in the family Scombridae , the mackerel family .
Archaeocindis johnbeckeri is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Archaeocindis .
Sinea is a New World genus of assassin bugs , in the subfamily Harpactorinae .
It has been theorized that Puumala virus , unlike other members of the genus Hantavirus , may also have lethal effects on its rodent host .
Based on 16S rRNA sequence analysis , Pedomicrobium is a bacterium that belongs to the family Hyphomicrobiaceae , within the order of Rhizobiales under the class of alphaproteobacteria , in the phylum Proteobacteria ( Garrity et al . , 2001 ) .
The Cabalian frog or Leyte slender stream frog ( Hylarana albotuberculata ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family .
The Dartford warbler ( Sylvia undata ) is a typical warbler from the warmer parts of western Europe and northwestern Africa .
Bulbine is a genus of plants in the family Xanthorrhoeaceae and subfamily Asphodeloideae , named for the bulb - shaped tuber of many species .
Aspidopleura is an extinct monotypic genus of parasitic wasp in the Eupelmidae subfamily Neanastatinae and at present , it contains the single species Aspidopleura baltica .
Anisomeria bistriata is a species of beetle in the family Dytiscidae , the only species in the genus Anisomeria .
Allen 's chipmunk ( Neotamias senex ) is a species of chipmunk .
The Walnut elimia , scientific name Elimia bellula , is a species of freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Pleuroceridae .
Deroceras is a taxonomic genus of small to medium sized air - breathing land slugs in the family Agriolimacidae .
The Angola river frog or common river frog ( Amietia angolensis ) is a species of frog in the Pyxicephalidae family .
Böhme 's mountain gecko , Alsophylax boehmei , is a species of gekkonid lizard endemic to South Asia .
Argent and sable moths or Rheumaptera hastata are day flying moths of the Geometridae family , with distinctive black and white colourings .
The Bean 's sawtooth eel ( Serrivomer beanii , also known commonly as the longfin sawpalate , the saw - tooth snipe eel , the sawtooth eel , the shortnosed snipe eel , and the stout sawpalate ) is an eel in the family Nemichthyidae ( snipe eels ) .
Leptosporangiate ferns are the largest group of living ferns , including some 11000 species worldwide .
The Anatolian vole ( Microtus anatolicus ) is a species of vole found in Turkey , specifically Konya Province .
Abacops rugipennis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Abacops .
Przewalski 's steppe lemming ( Eolagurus przewalskii ) is a species of rodents in the family Cricetidae .
Mormyrops is a genus of weakly electric fish in the family Mormyridae from freshwater in Africa .
Duguetia is a genus of trees and shrubs in the plant family Annonaceae with approximately 90 species in central and South America , and four species in west Africa .
Phormoestes is a genus of moths in the Choreutidae family , containing only one species , Phormoestes palmettovora , which is known from Florida , United States .
The Clarke 's weaver ( Ploceus golandi ) is a species of bird in the Ploceidae family .
Taheitia is a genus of very small land snails that have an operculum and live very near saltwater , maritime terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Truncatellidae .
The Kachin red - backed vole ( Eothenomys cachinus ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Carychiinae is part of the family Ellobiidae according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Coprophanaeoides is a genus of Scarabaeidae , or scarab beetles , in the superfamily , Scarabaeoidea .
In 1982 , Evans concluded that Hemiodoecus was , of known genera , the earliest evolved Australian genus of the Peloridiidae , based upon morphology and distribution .
Parastenomordella is a genus of South American beetles in the family Mordellidae , containing the following species :
Strioturbonilla is a small genus of very small sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs or micromolluscs in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies , and the subfamily Chrysallidinae , a large taxon of minute marine gastropods with an intorted protoconch .
Parajulidae is a family of millipedes in the order Julida , occurring predominantly in North America but also in Central America and East Asia .
The Spanish mole ( Talpa occidentalis ) is a species of mammal in the family Talpidae .
The Maracaibo wood turtle ( Rhinoclemmys diademata or Rhinoclemmys dademata ) is a species of turtles belonging to the Rhinoclemmys genus of the family Geoemydida found in Colombia and Venezuela .
The Wongai ningaui ( Ningaui ridei ) , also known as the Inland ningaui , is a small carnivorous marsupial native to Australia .
Amphigyra is a genus of air - breathing freshwater snail , an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails .
The Allodapini is a tribe of bees in the subfamily Xylocopinae , family Apidae .
King crabs are generally thought to be derived from hermit crab - like ancestors , which may explain the asymmetry still found in the adult forms .
Xenerpestes is the genus of greytails , birds in the family Furnariidae .
Paradactylodon is a genus of salamanders , known as the mountain salamanders or Middle Eastern stream salamanders , in the Hynobiidae family , endemic to Iran and Afghanistan .
Hemerocallidoideae is the botanical name of a subfamily of flowering plants , part of the family Xanthorrhoeaceae sensu lato in the monocot order Asparagales according to the APG system of 2009 .
The Mount Kahuzi climbing mouse ( Dendromus kahuziensis ) is a rodent found only in the Democratic Republic of the Congo .
Mixodectidae or mixodectids ( from Greek μιξο , mixo , `` mixed '' , and δεκτες , dektes `` biter '' ) is an extinct family of insectivore , placental mammals in the order Dermoptera .
The Maryland darter ( Etheostoma sellare ) is considered one of the rarest freshwater fish species in the world , due in part to its incredibly limited geographic range and difficulty of detection .
Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 simply included the Anomphalidae in `` basal taxa that are certainly Gastropoda '' .
Beecroft 's flying squirrel or Beecroft 's scaly - tailed squirrel ( Anomalurus beecrofti ) is a species of rodent in the family Anomaluridae .
Westcottia amorpha is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Westcottia .
The Koa Tao Island caecilian , Ichthyophis kohtaoensis , is a species of amphibian in the Ichthyophiidae family found in Cambodia , Laos , Myanmar , Thailand , and Vietnam .
The Taiwan saddled carpetshark , Cirrhoscyllium formosanum , is a carpetshark of the family Parascylliidae found around Taiwan , between latitudes 28 ° N and 21 ° N , at depths to 110 m. Its length is up to 39 cm . Reproduction is oviparous .
The Indian peafowl or blue peafowl ( Pavo cristatus ) , a large and brightly coloured bird , is a species of peafowl native to South Asia , but introduced in many other parts of the world .
The Coldwater elimia , scientific name Elimia modesta , is a species of freshwater snails with an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Pleuroceridae .
Thompsonella is a genus of family Crassulaceae .
Lasaeidae is a family of very small saltwater clams , marine bivalve molluscs in the superfamily Galeommatoidea .
Alphacoronaviruses are the first of the four genera , alpha- , beta- , gamma- , and delta - coronavirus in the subfamily Coronavirinae of the family Coronaviridae .
Sarcophrynium is a genus of plant in family Marantaceae indigenous to tropical Africa .
Pseudolarix is a monotypic genus of conifer in the family Pinaceae .
Burnup 's hunter slug ( Chlamydephorus burnupi ) is a species of land slug in the family Chlamydephoridae .

Chrysidea is a genus of cuckoo wasps belonging to the family Chrysididae .
The Bermuda flightless duck ( Anas pachyscelus ) is an extinct species of flightless duck which was endemic to the island of Bermuda in the North Atlantic Ocean .
Petrophytum cinerascens ( orth . var . Petrophyton cinerascens ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common names halfshrub rockmat and Chelan rockmat .
Pleuragramma antarcticum , the Antarctic silverfish , is a species of cod icefish native to the Southern Ocean .
The Maloideae C.Weber was the apple subfamily , a grouping used by some taxonomists within the rose family , Rosaceae .
Hubert 's multimammate mouse , or Hubert 's mastomys ( Mastomys huberti ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae found in Burkina Faso , Gambia , Mali , Mauritania , Nigeria , and Senegal , and possibly Guinea , Guinea - Bissau , and Niger .
Margarornis is the genus of treerunners , birds in the family Furnariidae .
Therasea was a genus of moths of the Noctuidae family , it is now considered a synonym of Tarache .
The Seychelles house snake ( Lamprophis geometricus ) is a species of snake in the Colubridae family .
Cynophalla is a genus of flowering plants in the caper family , Capparaceae , of about 20 species that are shrubs , trees , or vines .
The Pemba flying fox ( Pteropus voeltzkowi ) is a species of flying fox in the family Pteropodidae .
Teuchophorus is a known genus of fly in the family Dolichopodidae .
The Laboulbeniales is an order of Fungi within the class Laboulbeniomycetes .
The American lobster , Homarus americanus , is a species of lobster found on the Atlantic coast of North America , chiefly from Labrador to New Jersey .
The Eucla cod , Euclichthys polynemus , is a deepwater marine fish belonging to the cod order ( Gadiformes ) .
The Mayotte sunbird ( Cinnyris coquerellii ) is a species of bird in the Nectariniidae family .
The African emerald cuckoo ( Chrysococcyx cupreus ) is a species of cuckoo .
Vidrioceratinae is one of two subfamilies of the Vidrioceratidae Family .
Exocarpos is a genus of flowering shrubs and small trees in the sandalwood family , Santalaceae .
Membras is a genus of fish , Neotropical silversides , from freshwater , brackish water and marine habitats along the Atlantic coast of the Americas .
Urocyclidae is a family of air - breathing land snails and semi - slugs , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Helicarionoidea , ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Helena 's tree frog , Hyla helenae , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Guyana .
The Carpathian newt , or Montadon 's newt , ( Lissotriton montandoni ) is a species of salamander in the family Salamandridae found in Czech Republic , Poland , Romania , Slovakia , and Ukraine .
The Arnhem Land rock rat ( Zyzomys maini ) also known as the Arnhem Rock - rat and by the Indigenous Australian name of Kodjperr is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The family name derives from tupai , the Malay word for treeshrew and also for squirrel which the Tupaiidae superficially resemble .
The Mauritian wood pigeon ( Columba thiriouxi ) is an extinct species of the pigeon genus Columba which was endemic to Mauritius .
Actinostemon is a plant genus of the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1841 .
The Agulhas long - billed lark ( Certhilauda brevirostris ) is a small passerine bird .
The Prespa spirlin , Alburnoides prespensis , is a fish species of Cyprinidae family .
Rhizopogonaceae are a family of fungi in the order Boletales .
Burton 's gerbil , Gerbillus burtoni is distributed mainly in Darfur , Sudan .
Ascophora is an infraorder under order Cheilostomata of the Bryozoa .
Allantospermum is a genus of trees up to 90 m tall in family Ixonanthaceae .
Austroicetes is a genus in the subfamily Oedipodinae and family Acrididae .
Doryichthys , river pipefish , is a genus of Asian freshwater pipefishes .
Hexanodes vulgata is a species of beetle in the family Dermestidae , the only species in the genus Hexanodes .
Knipowitschia longecaudata , the Longtail dwarf goby , is a species of goby native to the Black Sea , Sea of Azov , and the Caspian Sea where it is mostly found in areas of brackish water over sand or amongst weeds where it feeds on small invertebrates .
Rissoina is a large genus of minute sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Rissoinidae .
Anemone parviflora ( Northern anemone , Small - flowered anemone ) is a herbaceous plant species in the genus Anemone and family Ranunculaceae .

Basilewskyana villiersi is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Basilewskyana .
Stypandra is a small genus of rhizomatous perennials in the family Xanthorrhoeaceae , subfamily Hemerocallidoideae .
Romanogobio vladykovi , also called Danube whitefin gudgeon , is a species of freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family .

Metopium is a genus of flowering plants in the sumac family , Anacardiaceae .
Gammacoronaviruses are one of the four genera , alpha , beta , gamma , and delta in the subfamily Coronavirinae of the family Coronaviridae .
Orazio Fagone ( born November 13 , 1968 in Catania ) is an Italian sledge hockey player and former short track speed skater who competed in the 1988 Winter Olympics , 1992 Winter Olympics and 1994 Winter Olympics .
Joanne Brown ( born 7 April 1972 in Canberra ) is a former softball catcher and outfielder from Australia , who won a bronze medal at the 1996 Summer Olympics and 2000 Summer Olympics .

Count Tivadar Batthyány de Németújvár ( February 23 , 1859 in Zalaszentgrót , Zala County -- February 2 , 1931 in Budapest ) son of Count Zsigmond Batthyány de Német - Ujvar , and Johanna Nepomucena Justina Maria Goberta Erdödy .

Henry S. Tyler ( September 20 , 1851 - January 14 , 1896 ) was Mayor of Louisville , Kentucky from 1891 to 1896 .

Jean - Baptiste Cotelier or Cotelerius ( born December , 1629 , Nîmes ; died 19 August 1686 , Paris ) was a Patristic scholar and Catholic theologian .
Josef Bachmeier survived the war and died on the 4 February 1971 in Sarstedt near Hanover .
Wladimiro Panizza ( Fagnano Olona , 5 June 1945 -- Cassano Magnago , 21 May 2002 ) was an Italian professional road bicycle racer .
Emil Reisch ( 28 September 1863 , Vienna -- 13 December 1933 , Vienna ) was an Austrian classical philologist and archaeologist .
Among a number of other schools named for Stevens , the Thaddeus Stevens Elementary School in Washington , D.C. was founded in 1868 as the first school built for African - American children there .
Giovanni Battista Natali was an Italian painter of the late - Baroque period , active in his natal city of Piacenza , but also Savona , Lucca , and Naples , and finally Genoa in 1736 .
Leandro Bisiach ( 1864 -- 1 December 1945 ) was an Italian violin maker , who was born in Casale Monferrato and died in 1945 at Venegono Superiore near Varese .
Nikiforos Lytras ( Greek : Νικηφόρος Λύτρας ; 1832 , Pyrgos , Tinos -- June 13 , 1904 , Athens ) was a nineteenth - century Greek painter .
Hugo Gräf ( born Rehestädt 10 October 1892 : died Gotha 23 October 1958 ) was a German Communist politician .
Robert Bodanzky , also known as Danton ( born 18 March 1879 in Vienna , Austria - Hungary as Isidor Bodanskie , died 2 November 1923 in Berlin , Germany ) , was an Austrian journalist , playwright , poet and artist .
Johann V of Nassau - Vianden - Dietz ( Breda , 9 November 1455 -- Dillenburg , 30 July 1516 ) was count of Nassau ( in Siegen , Dillenburg , Hadamar and Herborn ) , Vianden and Diez , and Lord of Breda .
Born in Beijing in January 1655 , Nalan Xingde came from a powerful Manchu family that not only belonged to the Plain Yellow Banner of the Eight Banners , but was also related to royalty .
Hermann Potschka was wounded during the Battle of Berlin and died in hospital on the 1 May 1945 .
Camilo García de Polavieja y del Castillo - Negrete , Marques de Polavieja ( 1838 - -1914 ) was a Spanish general born in Madrid on July 13 , 1838 , in a family of merchants .
Paine Wingate ( May 14 , 1739 -- March 7 , 1838 ) was an American preacher , farmer , and statesman from Stratham , New Hampshire .
Francisco Mendoza de Bobadilla died in 1566 in Arcos de la Llana , near Burgos .
Gilbert Dean ( August 14 , 1819 Pleasant Valley , Dutchess County , New York -- October 12 , 1870 Poughkeepsie , New York , Dutchess Co. , NY ) was an American lawyer and politician from New York .
Evaristo Carriego ( Paraná , May 7 , 1883 -- Buenos Aires , October 13 , 1912 ) , was an Argentine poet , best known for the biography written about him by Jorge Luis Borges .
Rinaldo Cuneo ( July 2 , 1877 -- December 27 , 1939 ) , dubbed the Painter of San Francisco , was an American artist known for his landscape paintings and murals .
Claude François Chauveau - Lagarde ( Chartres 1756 -- Paris 1841 ) came into the public spotlight in the early stages of the French Revolution .
Simone di Filippo Benvenuti , known as Simone dei Crocifissi or Simone da Bologna , ( Bologna , about 1330 - Bologna , 1399 ) , was an Italian painter .
Some historians believe that the Jianwen Emperor had indeed survived and escaped from Nanjing , but the official histories of the Ming dynasty were modified later during the Qing dynasty to please the Manchu rulers .
Piero Sraffa ( /ˈsræfə/ ; 5 August 1898 -- 3 September 1983 ) was an influential Italian economist , who served as lecturer of economics at the University of Cambridge .
Pentti Aalto ( July 22 , 1917 -- November 30 , 1998 ) was a Finnish linguist who was the University of Helsinki Docent of Comparative Linguistics 1958 - -1980 .
Marco Cornaro ( c. 1286 -- 13 January 1368 ) , also known as Marco Corner , was the 59th doge of Venice , ruling between 1365 and 1368 .
Carlotta Patti died of cancer in Paris on 27 June 1889 .
Otto Stoll ( December 29 , 1849 in Frauenfeld -- August 18 , 1922 in Zürich ) was a Swiss linguist and ethnologist .
Helen Van Pelt Wilson died in Wilton , Connecticut , on September 30 , 2003 .
Ivan Triesault ( born as Johann Constantin Treisalt ; 13 July ( O.S. 1 July ) 1898 in Reval ( now Tallinn ) -- January 3 , 1980 in Los Angeles ) was an Estonian - born American actor .
Alfredo D'Ambrosio ( Naples , 13 June 1871 -- Nice , 29 December 1914 ( or Paris , 31 December 1914 ) ) was an Italian composer and violinist .
Carlo Karges ( 31 July 1951 in Hamburg -- 30 January 2002 in Hamburg ) was a German musician who became a guitarist and songwriter for the rock band , Nena .
Daniel Webster Marsh ( August 15 , 1838 -- June 27 , 1916 ) was a businessman and mayor of Calgary , Alberta , Canada .
Adrien Marquet ( 6 October 1885 -- 3 February 1955 ) was a socialist mayor of Bordeaux who turned to the far right .
Iskandar Khatloni ( Persian : اسکندر ختلانی‎ ; October 1954 -- September 22 , 2000 ) was a journalist from Tajikistan who worked for Radio Free Europe and was murdered in Moscow , Russia while covering the Second Chechen War .
Marius Canard ( Dracy - Saint - Loup , 26 December 1888 -- Paris , September 1982 ) was a French Orientalist and historian .
Hannah Ocuish ( March 1774-December 1786 ) was executed at the age of twelve years and nine months , being hanged on 20 December 1786 , in New London , Connecticut .
Colard Mansion was a central figure in the early printing industry in Bruges .
Bernhard Christoph Breitkopf ( 2 March 1695 in Clausthal , now Clausthal - Zellerfeld -- 26 March 1777 in Leipzig ) was a German printer and publisher , and founder of the publisher that became Breitkopf & Härtel .
Pietro Mocenigo ( 1406 - -1476 ) was doge of Venice from 1474 to 1476 .
Born in Dublin in 1917 , Kevin Boland was the son of Gerald Boland , a founder - member of Fianna Fáil , and the nephew of Harry Boland .
Titia Brongersma ( Dokkum , Friesland , 1650 -- Groningen , 1700 ) was a Frisian poet of the late 17th century .
Donald Douglas Lamond , Jr. ( August 18 , 1920 , Oklahoma City - December 23 , 2003 , Orlando , Florida ) , better known as Don Lamond , was an American jazz drummer .

Ferdinand Avenarius ( 20 December 1856 in Berlin -- 22 September 1923 in Kampen ) was a lyric poet , a leading representative of the culture reform movement of his time and the first popularizer of Sylt .
Raphael Sealey ( 14 August 1927 , Middlesbrough , England -- 29 November 2013 , Berkeley , California ) was a classical scholar and ancient historian .
Alexandre Arsène Girault ( /ʒiːˈroʊ/ zhee - ROW ; 9 January 1884 , Annapolis -- 2 May 1941 , Brisbane ) was an American entomologist specialising in the study of chalcid wasps .
Nikolay Milyutin was born in Moscow on June 6 , 1818 , the scion of an influential , but impoverished , aristocratic Russian family .
Vilém Kurz ( 1872 , Německý Brod ( Havlíčkův Brod ) , Bohemia -- 1945 ) was a Czech pianist and piano teacher , a professor at the State Conservatory in Lwów and Vienna , and Prague Conservatory .
Abu al - Wafa Ali Ibn Aqil ibn Ahmad al - Baghdadi ( 1040 - -1119 ) was an Islamic theologian from Baghdad , Iraq .
Michael Maestlin ( also Mästlin , Möstlin , or Moestlin ) ( 30 September 1550 , Göppingen -- 20 October 1631 , Tübingen ) was a German astronomer and mathematician , known for being the mentor of Johannes Kepler .
Johannes Hermanus Koekkoek , ( Veere , 17 August 1778 -- Amsterdam , 9 January 1851 ) was a Dutch painter and draughtsman .
The Wanli Emperor died in 1620 and was buried in the Dingling Mausoleum among the Ming tombs on the outskirts of Beijing .
After a brief illness Primo Riccitelli died on the 27th of March , 1941 in Giulianova where he is now buried .
Zsigmond Vincze ( Hungarian : Vincze Zsigmond ) ( 1 July 1874 in Zombor -- 30 June 1935 in Budapest ) was a Hungarian pianist , conductor and composer who wrote several very successful operettas .
Doreen Norton , OBE , FRCN ( 1 May 1922 , Dartford , Kent -- 30 December 2007 , Worthing , West Sussex ) was an English nurse , in the 1950s she used research to show that the best treatment and prevention of bedsores was removing the pressure by turning the patient .
Siaosi Tupou II , King of Tonga ( George Tupou II in English ) ( 17 July 1874 -- 17 July 1918 ) was the King of Tonga from 18 February 1893 until his death .

Llorenç Villalonga i Pons ( Palma de Mallorca , March 1 , 1897 -- January 27 , 1980 ) was a Spanish writer and psychiatrist .
