Elov Persson died in his native Gävleborg County 's Torsåker Parish , one day before his 76th birthday .
King Kolax ( November 6 , 1912 , Kansas City , Missouri -- December 18 , 1991 , Chicago , Illinois ) was a United States jazz trumpeter .
Zacharie Astruc ( 20 February 1833 , Angers -- 24 May 1907 , Paris ) was a French sculptor , painter , poet , and art critic .
Aleksander Arulaid ( 24 May 1924 , Tallinn -- 8 July 1995 , Tallinn ) was an Estonian chess player , who three times won the Estonian Chess Championship .
Hendrik Enno Boeke ( 12 September 1881 , Wormerveer -- 6 December 1918 , Frankfurt am Main ) was a Dutch mineralogist and petrographer .
Kurt Schlosser ( 18 October 1900 -- 16 August 1944 in Dresden ) was German cabinet - maker , climber , and an active Communist .
Juozas Maniušis ( 15 December 1910 in Mogilev Governorate -- 17 March 1987 in Vilnius ) was a communist politician in the Lithuanian SSR specializing in areas of industry , construction , and engineering .
Robert Erickson ( March 7 , 1917 in Marquette , Michigan -- April 24 , 1997 in San Diego , California ) was an American composer .
Jack Sangster died in Belgravia , London , from cancer on 26 March 1977 .
Princess Romanework Haile Selassie , sometimes spelt as Romane Work Haile Selassie ( died in Turin on 14 October 1940 ) , was the eldest child of Emperor Haile Selassie of Ethiopia by his first wife , Woizero Altayech .
Wiesław Adam Berger ( 6 June 1926 in Ostrava - Přívoz -- 15 January 1998 in Ostrava ) was a Polish writer connected with the Zaolzie region of Cieszyn Silesia .

Ah Lum ( before 1909 - -1925 ) was a gold miner and store owner in Arrowtown , New Zealand .

Sir William Forbes of Callendar ( 1756 - -1823 ) was a prosperous coppersmith and landowner who lived in Callendar House in Falkirk , Scotland .
Niels Hemmingsen ( Nicolaus Hemmingius ) ( 1513 in Taagerup -- 1600 in Roskilde ) was a Danish Lutheran theologian .
Jean Giraud was born in Nogent - sur - Marne , Val - de - Marne , in the suburbs of Paris , on 8 May 1938 .
Juan Rogelio García García , better known as Juan Orol ( August 4 , 1897 in Lalín , Pontevedra , Spain -- May 26 , 1988 in Mexico City , Mexico ) was a Mexican - Spanish actor , producer , screenwriter and film director .
Pedro Adolfo de Castro was a twentieth - century architect from San Juan , Puerto Rico .
Jerrold Robertshaw ( 28 March 1866 in Allerton , West Riding of Yorkshire -- died 14 February 1941 in London ) was a British stage and film actor of the silent era .

Enrique Ballesté ( Mexico City , October 10 , 1946 -- September 19 , 2015 ) was a Mexican actor , playwright , composer and theatrical producer .
Major Lewis Ginter ( April 24 , 1824 -- October 1 , 1897 ) was a prominent businessman , military officer , real estate developer , and philanthropist centered in Richmond , Virginia .
Ettore Tolomei ( 16 August 1865 in Rovereto -- 25 May 1952 in Rome ) was an Italian nationalist and fascist .
Danica Seleskovitch died in Cahors ( France ) on April 17 , 2001 , in her 80th year .

Hermann von Mallinckrodt attended the gymnasium at Aachen and studied law at Berlin and Bonn .

Peter Faneuil ( June 20 , 1700 -- March 3 , 1743 ) was a wealthy American colonial merchant , slave trader , and philanthropist who donated Faneuil Hall to Boston .
Donald B. Steinaker ( 1922 - -1942 ) was a United States Marine Corps private first class who received a posthumous Navy Cross for his actions in the Guadalcanal campaign during World War II . Donald Baur Steinaker was born at Syracuse , New York , on 15 September 1922 .
Gustav Nikolaus Tiedemann ( February 17 , 1808 Landshut , Bavaria - August 11 , 1849 Rastatt ) was a German soldier who joined the revolutionaries during the Revolutions of 1848 in Germany , eventually becoming the commander of the last holdout of the revolution , the fortress at Rastatt .
Keith Alfred Hindwood ( 1904 - 1971 ) was a Sydney - based Australian businessman and amateur ornithologist .
Alvise I Mocenigo ( 26 October 1507 -- 4 June 1577 ) was doge of Venice from 1570 to 1577 .
Gerasimos Pitsamanos or Pitzamanos ( Greek : Γεράσιμος Πιτσαμάνος/Πιτζαμάνος ; 6 March 1787 , Argostoli - 5 December 1825 , Corfu ) was a Greek architect and portrait painter .
Earl Baldwin ( January 11 , 1901 in Newark , New Jersey -- October 9 , 1970 in Hollywood , California , age 69 ) was an American screenwriter .
Frederick IV , Landgrave of Thuringia , nicknamed Frederick the Peaceful or Frederick the Simple , the peaceful one , and the Fool ( before 30 November 1384 -- 7 May 1440 at Runneburg Castle in Weißensee ) was a member of the House of Wettin and was Margrave of Meissen and Landgrave of Thuringia .
Max Pallenberg ( born December 18 , 1877 , as Max Pollack in Vienna - June 26 , 1934 , in Karlovy Vary ) was an Austrian singer , actor and comedian .
Piermassimiliano Dotto , also known as Piero Dotto ( Treviso , 28 February 1970 - Volpago del Montello , 25 October 2012 ) , was an Italian rugby union player .
Cao Pi ( 187 -- 29 June 226 ) , courtesy name Zihuan , was the first emperor of the state of Cao Wei in the Three Kingdoms period .
John H. Eastman ( September 23 , 1861 -- November 14 , 1938 ) was a businessman who served from 1910 - -1914 as the mayor of Shreveport , the third largest city in Louisiana and the largest in the northwestern section of the state .
Rudolf Bredow ( born 2 November 1909 in Berlin , died 17 November 1973 in Bremen ) , German post - expressionist painter , draughtsman and art teacher .

Charles Henri Ford ( February 10 , 1908 -- September 27 , 2002 ) was an American poet , novelist , filmmaker , photographer , and collage artist best known for his editorship of the Surrealist magazine View ( 1940 - -1947 ) in New York City , and as the partner of the artist Pavel Tchelitchew .
Samuel Crompton was born at 10 Firwood Fold , Bolton , Lancashire to George and Betty Crompton ( née Elizabeth Holt of Turton ) .

Renato Bodini ( October 1 , 1909 in Cremona -- August 23 , 1974 in Rome ) was an Italian professional football player and coach .

Franz Josef Popp ( January 14 , 1886 in Vienna -- July 29 , 1954 in Stuttgart ) was one of three men responsible for the founding of BMW AG and the First General Director of BMW AG from 1922 to 1942 .
Pedro Pérez Delgado ( 1881 , Ospino , Estado Portuguesa , Venezuela - 7 November 1924 , Puerto Cabello , Venezuela ) , better known as Maisanta , was a nineteenth - century Venezuelan revolutionary and politician .
Cándido López ( 29 August 1840 , Buenos Aires - 31 December 1902 , Baradero ) was an Argentinian photographer , soldier and painter , who worked in the Naïve style .
Ray Linn ( born October 20 , 1920 in Chicago , Illinois - died November 1996 in Columbus , Ohio ) was an American jazz trumpeter .
Theophil Großgebauer ( 24 November 1627 , Ilmenau -- 8 July 1661 , Rostock ) was a German Lutheran theologian active at the University of Rostock , most notable for his work Wächterstimme aus dem verwüsteten Zion .
Ernst Erwin Oehme ( 18 September 1831 , in Dresden -- 10 October 1907 , Blasewitz ) was a German painter .

Tommaso Martini ( Bivongi , Calabria , 1688 -- 5 January 1755 ) was an Italian painter of the late - Baroque period .

Lotte Laserstein ( November 28 , 1898 in Preussisch Holland , German Empire -- January 21 , 1993 in Kalmar , Sweden ) was a German - Swedish painter and portraitist .

Lillian Kemble - Cooper ( March 21 , 1892 in London , England -- May 4 , 1977 in Los Angeles , USA ) was a British actress .

Charles Nègre ( French : ( nɛɡʁ ) ; 9 May 1820 -- 16 January 1880 ) was a pioneering photographer , born in Grasse , France .
Joseph Sokolsky ( Bulgarian : Йосиф Соколски , Gabrovo , 1786 -- died on Kiev , now Ukraine September 30 , 1879 ) was the first Bulgarian clergyman to convert to Catholicism and a pioneer of the Bulgarian Uniat Church .

Diego von Bergen died on October 7 , 1944 , in Wiesbaden , Germany ; his death was announced ten days later in L'Osservatore Romano , in an obituary which called him `` highly esteemed and unanimously liked '' .
Countess Anna Fridrica Wilhelmina von Hallwyl , née Kempe ( 1 October 1844 − 25 July 1930 ) was a Swedish collector and donor whose accumulation of art and other objects constitute the current Hallwyl Museum in Stockholm .
Giovanni Pietro Perti or Peretti ( 1648 in Muggio , Switzerland -- 1714 in Vilnius , Lithuania ) was an Italian Baroque sculptor and architect , regarded as one of the leading European sculptors on the verge of the 18th century .

Johann Eduard Karsen ( 10 March 1860 , Amsterdam - 31 October 1941 , Amsterdam ) was a Dutch Post - impressionist painter , known for his moody scenes featuring villages and farmhouses ; usually containing a solitary figure .
Julius Ebbinghaus ( 9 November 1885 , Berlin -- 16 June 1981 , Marburg an der Lahn ) was a German philosopher , one of the closest followers of Immanuel Kant active in the twentieth century .
Ladislav František Čelakovský ( December 3 , 1863 -- December 31 , 1916 ) was a Czech mycologist and botanist born in Prague .
Konstantin Bogaevsky was born in the Eastern Crimean city of Feodosiya ( currently Ukraine ) to an old Italian - German family of the Genoese extraction on 24 January ( O.S. 12 January ) 1872 .
Berthold Englisch ( 9 July 1851 , Osoblaha -- 19 October 1897 , Vienna ) was a leading Austrian chess master .
Luigi Ruffo - Scilla JUD ( 25 August 1750 -- 17 November 1832 ) was a Cardinal of the Holy Roman Church who served as Apostolic Nuncio to Austria and Archbishop of Naples .
Joseph Paneth ( 6 October 1857 -- 4 January 1890 ) was an Austrian physiologist born in Vienna .
Ali Suat Hayri Ürgüplü ( 13 August 1903 , Damascus , Ottoman Empire -- 26 December 1981 , Istanbul , Turkey ) was a Turkish political figure .
Rev. Dr. Hermann Gundert ( Stuttgart , 4 February 1814 -- 25 April 1893 in Calw , Germany ) was a German missionary , scholar , and linguist , as well as the grandfather of German novelist and Nobel laureate Hermann Hesse .

Milo Dor ( born 7 March 1923 as Milutin Doroslovac in Budapest ; died 5 December 2005 in Vienna ) was a writer and translator .

Adolf Lindenbaum ( June 12 , 1904 in Warsaw , Kingdom of Poland , Russian Empire ( now Poland ) -- 1941 in Paneriai ) , was a Polish logician and mathematician .

Ernst Hechler died on 23 October 1965 aged 57 in Alzey , Federal Republic of Germany .
Norman O. Houston was a prominent Los Angeles - based businessman and president of Golden State Mutual Life Insurance Company , which at one time was the largest black - owned business west of the Mississippi .

Nellie Mae Rowe ( July 4 , 1900 -- October 18 , 1982 ) was an African - American self - taught artist from Fayette , Georgia .

Aleksandar Nikolić died on 12 March 2000 , in Belgrade , He is buried in the Alley of the Greats , in Belgrade , Novo Groblje ( `` New Cemetery '' ) .
Red McKenzie ( William McKenzie ) ( October 14 , 1899 , St. Louis , Missouri - February 7 , 1948 , New York City ) was an American jazz musician .
Francis van Bossuit ( 1635 , Brussels -- 1692 , Amsterdam ) , was a Flemish sculptor , working mostly in terracotta , wood , and ivory .
Adolf Grabowsky ( August 31 , 1880 , Berlin - August 23 , 1969 , Arlesheim , Switzerland ) was a German political scientist and author of several books about geopolitics and political theory , including `` Democracy and Dictatorship '' ( 1949 ) .
Eneas Perdomo died at the Military Hospital located in the city of Caracas , after a long illness .
Professor Nadav Safran ( Arabic : نداف صفران‎ , Hebrew : נדב ספרן‎ , August 25 , 1925 , Cairo -- July 5 , 2003 , State College , PA ) was an expert in Arab and Middle East politics and a director of Harvard 's Center for Middle Eastern Studies .
Born in Belo Horizonte , capital of the state of Minas Gerais , Roberto Batata started his professional career playing for América - MG , leaving the club to join Cruzeiro in 1969 .
Velibor Jonić ( Serbian Cyrillic : Велибор Јонић ; 12 February 1892 -- 17 July 1946 ) was a Serbian fascist politician and government minister in the Territory of the Military Commander in Serbia during World War II . He taught at the Military Academy in Belgrade and at the Yugoslav royal court before the war .
Mary Toft ( née Denyer ; c. 1701 - -1763 ) , also spelled Tofts , was an English woman from Godalming , Surrey , who in 1726 became the subject of considerable controversy when she tricked doctors into believing that she had given birth to rabbits .
Eugeniusz Kwiatkowski ( 30 December 1888 in Kraków -- 22 August 1974 in Kraków ) was a Polish politician and economist , Deputy Prime Minister of Poland , government minister and manager of the Second Polish Republic .
Boris Goldstein ( Busya Goldshtein ) ( 25 of December 1922 , Odessa - 8 of November 1987 , Hanover , Germany ) was a Soviet violinist whose career was greatly hindered by the political situation in the USSR .
Joaquín Albareda y Ramoneda was born in Barcelona to Vicente Albareda and his wife María Ramoneda .
Hüseyin Avni Zaimler ( 1877 , Bitola -- March 10 , 1930 , Adana ) , known as Huseyin Avni Bey or Huseyin Avni Pasha , was an officer of the Ottoman Army and a general of the Turkish Army .
Jules Brévié died at the age of 84 on 28 July 1964 in the village of Pierrefitte near Talizat , Cantal .
An institute in Wrocław , Poland called the Włodzimierz Trzebiatowski Institute of Low Temperature and Structure Research is named after him .
Gregg G. Tallas ( Greek : Γκρέκ Τάλλας , born Γρηγόρης Θαλασσινός , Grigoris Thalassinos ; January 25 , 1909 , Athens -- February 1 , 1993 , Athens ) was a film director from Greece .
Paul Barrière was born on 8 June 1920 in Espéraza and died on 29 May 2008 in Biarritz , aged 88 .
Jacques Barbeu - Dubourg ( 12 February 1709 , Mayenne -- 14 December 1779 , Paris ) was a French physician , botanist , writer , translator and publisher known for translating Benjamin Franklin 's work into French and for inventing a gentlemen 's umbrella fitted with a lightning conductor .
Olivier Gendebien died in 1998 at his home in Les Baux - de - Provence in southern France .
Julius Leopold Pagel ( 29 May 1851 , Pollnow -- 30 January 1912 , Berlin ) was a German physician and historian of medicine .
Count August Zamoyski ( June 28 , 1893 in Jabłoń , Lublin Voivodeship , Poland -- May 19 , 1970 in Saint - Clar - de - Rivière , France ) was a Polish sculptor , member of groups Bunt and Formiści .
Valentin Weigel ( or Weichel ; 7 August 1533 , in Hayn -- 10 June 1588 , in Zschopau ) was a German theologian , philosopher and mystical writer , from Saxony , and an important precursor of later theosophy .
Volkert Simon Maarten van der Willigen ( Rockanje , 9 May 1822 -- Haarlem , 19 February 1878 ) , sometimes referred to as Volcardus Simon Martinus van der Willigen , was a Dutch mathematician , physicist and professor .
Charles - Frédéric Soehnée ( Born 3 . November 1789 in Landau in der Pfalz as Carl - Friederich Söhne ; died 1 . May 1878 in Le Pré - Saint - Gervais in Paris ) was a French painter .
Géraud de Cordemoy ( 6 October 1626 , Paris -- 15 October 1684 , Paris ) was a French philosopher , historian and lawyer .
Alekos Sakellarios ( Greek : Αλέκος Σακελλάριος , 7 November 1913 in Athens -- 28 August 1991 in Athens ) was a Greek writer and a director .
John Frowen ( 11 October 1931 -- 28 August 2011 ) was a professional footballer who played for Cardiff City , Bristol Rovers and Newport County .
Hans H. Indorf ( died March 10 , 1989 in Fairfax , Virginia ) was an academic professor and international advisor in political science .
Stanislovas Kęsgaila was the Elder of Samogitia ( 1486 - -1522 ) , Grand Hetman of Lithuania ( 1501 - -1502 ) , castellan of Trakai ( 1499 - -1522 ) and Vilnius ( 1522 - -1526 ) .
Despite being only being thirty years old when he retired , Zhang Honggen would eventually move to management with Beijing Youth Team in 1970 .
Alejandro Rodríguez de Valcárcel y Nebreda , 1st Count of Rodríguez de Valcárcel ( 25 December 1917 in Burgos -- 22 November 1976 in Madrid ) was a Francoist Spanish politician , who served in important positions under Francisco Franco .
Max Švabinský ( 1873 - -1962 ) was a Czech painter , draughtsman , graphic artist , and professor in Academy of Graphic Arts in Prague .
Virgil von Graben ( 15th century -- 1507 ) was an Austrian noble and knight , who was stadtholder of Lienz and East Tyrol and Regent ( captain ) and stadtholder of Görz .
Sir Harold Spencer Jones KBE FRS ( 29 March 1890 Kensington , London -- 3 November 1960 ) was an English astronomer .
Marcellus Hartley Dodge Jr. ( July 29 , 1908 -- August 29 , 1930 ) was the heir to the Remington - Rockefeller fortune who died in a car accident in France .
Marcel Samuel - Rousseau ( 18 August 1882 Paris -- 11 June 1955 Paris ) was a French composer , organist , and opera director .
Pierre - Georges Castex ( 20 June 1915 at Toulouse -- 9 December 1995 at Paris ) was a French academic , literary critic and author .
James Nutcombe Gould ( known as Nutcombe Gould ) ( 24 February 1849 in Stoke - in - Teignhead , Devon -- 10 October 1899 in Paddington ) was an English stage actor .
Jacob Bjerknes lectured at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology during the 1933 - 1934 school year and emigrated to the United States in 1940 where he headed a government - sponsored meteorology annex for weather forecasting , at the department of physics of the University of California , Los Angeles .
Don Manuel Carrillo Tablas was a philanthropist and served as mayor of Orizaba , Veracruz , Mexico .
Edwin Hatch ( September 4 , 1835 Derby , England -- November 10 , 1889 Oxford , England ) was an English theologian .
Joseph A. McDonough ( 20 October 1896 - 11 May 1944 ) was an assistant director in Hollywood , perhaps most noted for working often with James Whale , even after Whale left Universal Studios .

Ekrem Bora , né Ekrem Şerif Uçak ( 7 March 1934 Ankara -- 1 April 2012 Istanbul ) was a Turkish film actor .

Kazimierz Rudzki ( born January 6 , 1911 in Warsaw - died February 2 , 1976 in Warsaw , Poland ) was a Polish stage and film actor , theatre director .

Gratien Le Père ( Versailles , 2 June 1769 - Poitiers , 1 August 1826 ) was a French civil engineer .
Ilya Livykou or Ilia Livykou ( Greek : Ίλυα Λιβυκού ; 1919 in Heraklio -- September 6 , 2002 in Athens , Greece ) was a Greek actress , a partner with Vassilis Logothetidis .

Karl - Gustav Kaisla ( 4 October 1943 in Helsinki -- 21 September 2012 in Helsinki ) was a Finnish ice hockey referee .

Derek Waring died from cancer at Petworth Cottage Hospital in West Sussex in 2007 , aged 79 .
Sylvia Fine Kaye died of emphysema at the age of 78 in her Manhattan apartment in 1991 .
Piero Camporesi ( Forlì , 15 February 1926 -- Bologna , 1997 ) was an Italian historian of literature and an anthropologist .
His family 's summer home at Talcottville , New York , known as Edmund Wilson House , was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1973 .
Francesc Xavier Bultó Marquès ( Barcelona , 17 May 1912 -- Barcelona , 3 August 1998 ) , popularly known as Paco Bultó , was a Catalan businessman , founder of Montesa Honda ( along with Peter Permanyer ) and Bultaco .
Auguste Gougeard ( 15 November 1827 -- 10 March 1886 , Paris ) was a French counsellor , naval officer and politician .
Ludwig Thoma ( 21 January 1867 , Oberammergau -- 26 August 1921 , Tegernsee ) was a German author , publisher and editor , who gained popularity through his partially exaggerated description of everyday Bavarian life .
Paul Dungler ( Thann , Haut - Rhin , 1902 - Colmar , 1974 ) was a French industrialist , royalist militant and Resistance worker .
Willard Hall ( December 24 , 1780 - May 10 , 1875 ) , was an American lawyer and politician from Wilmington , in New Castle County , Delaware .
Dienekes or Dieneces ( Greek : Διηνέκης ) was a Spartan soldier who fought and was killed at the Battle of Thermopylae in 480 BC . He was acclaimed the bravest of all the Greeks who fought in that battle .
Heinrich Brandt ( 8 November 1886 , Feudingen - 9 October 1954 , Halle , Saxony - Anhalt ) was a German mathematician who was the first to develop the concept of a groupoid .
Oldřich František Korte ( 26 April 1926 ; Šaľa , Slovakia -- 10 September 2014 ; Prague ) was a Czech composer , pianist , publicist and writer .

Jan Kunc ( 27 March 1883 , Doubravice nad Svitavou -- 11 September 1976 , Brno ) was a Czech composer , teacher , and writer .
In 2013 , a street in the Canberra suburb of Casey was named Kingsland Parade in Richard Kingsland 's honour .
Anton Laurids Johannes Dorph , usually known as Anton Dorph ( 15 February 1831 , Horsens - 12 January 1914 , Copenhagen ) was a Danish painter who is remembered for his altarpieces and his paintings of fishermen .
Carl Ashby ( 1914 - -2004 ) was an American abstract expressionist artist who lived and worked in New York City .
Ernst Gottlieb von Steudel ( 30 May 1783 , Esslingen am Neckar -- 12 May 1856 ) was a German physician and an authority on grasses .

Johann Conrad Beissel ( March 1 , 1691 -- July 6 , 1768 ) was the German - born religious leader who in 1732 founded the Ephrata Community in Pennsylvania , USA .
Eudoxe Marcille ( 20 April 1814 , Chartres - 7 April 1890 , Chécy ) was a French painter , museum director , art school director and art collector .
George Sylvester Viereck ( December 31 , 1884 , Munich , Germany -- died March 18 , 1962 , Holyoke , Massachusetts ) was a German - American poet , writer , and pro - Nazi propagandist .
Attila Szekrényessy ( born 20 January 1913 in Budapest , Hungary ; died February 1995 in Gyöngyös ) was a Hungarian pair skater who competed with his sister Piroska Szekrényessy .
Moyshe Altman ( Yiddish : משה אַלטמאַן‎ ; Russian : Моисей Элевич Альтман ) ( May 7 , 1890 , Lipcani , Bessarabia - October 21 , 1981 , Chernivtsi , USSR ) was a Yiddish writer .
Reinhard Opitz died of cancer in Cologne , where he had lived for twenty years .

Marcello Creti ( born in Rome on 16 April 1922 ; died in Sutri on 1 January 2000 ) was an Italian inventor , gem prospector , and reported healer who for a time led a group in a farm called Sapientia .

Paul Hermann ( 30 June 1646 , Halle -- 29 January 1695 , Leiden ) was a German born physician and botanist who for 15 years was director of the Hortus Botanicus Leiden .

Max Gold ( born Vienna , Austria ; died Tehran , Iran ) was an early twentieth century Austrian football ( soccer ) right full back who played professionally in Austria and the United States .
Andrija Paltašić ( Italian : Andrea Paltasichi Latin Andreas de Paltasichis ; Kotor 1440 -- Venice 1500 ) was a Venetian printer and publisher who was active from 1476 to 1492 .

Mahmut Atalay ( March 30 , 1934 , Çorum -- December 4 , 2004 , Ankara ) was a renowned Turkish World champion and Olympic medalist sports wrestler in the Welterweight class ( 73 kg until 1961 , 78 kg from 1961 on ) and a trainer who was born in Corum , Turkey .
James Pounder Whitney ( 30 November 1857 , Marsden , West Yorkshire -- 17 June 1939 , Cambridge ) was a British ecclesiastical historian .
Camille Libar ( 27 December 1917 -- 10 October 1991 ) in Dudelange ) is a former football player and manager from Luxembourg .

Jorge Loring Martinez ( Malaga , Spain , October 12 , 1889 -- Madrid , Spain , September 22 , 1936 ) was a Spanish engineer and entrepreneur , pioneer of civil aviation in that country , and considered by the Spanish Patent Office one of their great inventors .
Arsène Darmesteter ( 5 January 1846 , Château - Salins , Moselle -- 16 November 1888 , Paris ) was a distinguished French philologist and man of letters .
Magdalene Sibylle of Holstein - Gottorp ( also spelled Magdalena Sibylla ; 1631 at Gottorp Castle -- 1719 in Güstrow ) was a Duchess of Hostein - Gottorp by birth and by marriage Duchess of Mecklenburg - Güstrow .

Mavrocordat ) , born in Constantinople on 23 July 1684 and dead in Bucharest on 23 February 1719 , was caimacam of Moldavia ( 7 October 1711 -- 16 November 1711 ) and Prince of Wallachia between 2 December 1716 and 23 February 1719 .

George Kirke Spoor ( December 18 , 1871 -- 24 November 1953 ) was an early film pioneer who , with Gilbert M. `` Broncho Billy '' Anderson , founded Essanay Studios in Chicago in 1907 .

Vilhelm Lundstrøm ( 1893 , Copenhagen -- 1950 ) was one of Denmark 's most successful modernist painters .

John B. Clymer ( March 6 , 1887 - May 24 , 1937 ) was a Hollywood film screenwriter .
John Smybert ( or Smibert ) ( 1688 - -1751 ) was a Scottish American artist , who was born in Edinburgh , Scotland and died in Boston , Massachusetts , United States .

Juan Carlos Altavista ( January 4 , 1929 in Buenos Aires -- July 20 , 1989 ) was an Argentine actor and comedian .
Mladen III Šubić ( Croatian : Mladen III . Šubić ) ( c. 1315 -- Trogir , 1 May 1348 ) was a member of the Croatian Šubić noble family , who ruled from Klis Fortress .
Václav Hladík ( August 22 , 1868 in Prague - April 29 , 1913 in Prague ) was a Czech novelist , journalist and translator .
Gladys Castelvecchi ( born November 26 , 1922 in Rocha , Uruguay and died on May 28 , 2008 in Montevideo ) was an Uruguayan poet and literature professor .
Pilot Colonel Jacinto Rodríguez Díaz ( Totonicapán , 16 August 1901 -- Guatemala City , 28 September 1929 ) was one of the aviation pioneers in Guatemala .
Claude Barrett ( 5 December 1907 -- 3 August 1976 ) was an English footballer who played in the Football League for Bradford Park Avenue , Port Vale and York City .
Prince Pavel Yengalychev or Engalytshev ( Russian : Павел Николаевич Енгалычев ; 25 March 1864 -- 12 August 1944 , Lausanne ) was a Russian prince and general .

Hans Imhoff ( March 12 , 1922 -- December 21 , 2007 ) was a German chocolate producer and founder of the Imhoff - Schokoladenmuseum ( Imhoff Chocolate Museum ) in Cologne , Germany .
Gaspard Dughet ( 15 June 1615 -- 27 May 1675 ) , also known as Gaspard Poussin , was a French painter born in Rome .

Kazimierz Jelski ( 1782 -- March 1867 in Vilnius , Lithuania ) was a Polish Classicist architect and sculptor active in Lithuania .

Oluf Braren was born in Oldsum on Föhr in North Frisia .
Felice Nazzaro ( 4 December 1881 - 21 March 1940 ) was an Italian racecar driver , a native of Turin .
Pietro Perna ( 1519 -- August 16 , 1582 ) was an Italian printer , the leading printer of Late Renaissance Basel , the Erasmian crossroads between Italian Renaissance humanism and the Protestant Reformation .
Pavel Wonka ( January 21 , 1953 in Vrchlabí -- April 24 , 1988 in Hradec Králové ) was a Czechoslovak dissident of partly German origin and a victim of communist terror .
Joyce McDougall ( /məkˈduːɡəl/ ; 26 April 1920 , Dunedin , New Zealand -- 24 August 2011 , London , UK ) was a New Zealand - French psychoanalyst .

Nicola Fergola ( 1753 - 1824 ) was a mathematician from Italy professor in the university of Naples .
Georg Christian August Kestner ( 28 November 1777 in Hanover ; 5 March 1853 in Rome ) was a German diplomat and art collector .
Dieter Noll died in the night of February 6 of cancer in Zeuthen .
Earl Irvin West ( May 18 , 1920 , Carmel , Indiana -- February 4 , 2011 , Memphis , Tennessee ) was a historian of the Restoration Movement .
Carlos Pau y Español ( 1857 , Segorbe , Spain -- 1937 , Segorbe ) was a Spanish botanist .
Violet Mersereau died on November 12 , 1975 in Plymouth , Massachusetts , at the age of 83 .
Mathieu Matégot died at Angers , France in February 2001 .
Edward Joseph Kelly ( May 1 , 1876 -- October 20 , 1950 ) served as chief engineer of the Chicago Sanitary District in the 1920s , and later as mayor of Chicago , Illinois ( 1933 - -1947 ) ; he was a Democrat .
Abbé Joseph - Antoine Boullan ( Saint - Porquier , Tarn - et - Garonne , 18 February 1824 -- 4 January 1893 , Lyon ) was a French Roman Catholic priest and later a laicized priest , who is often accused of being a Satanist although he continued to defend his status as a Christian .

Saint Felix of Como ( died c. 390 AD ) is venerated as the first bishop of Como , on October 8 , 391 .
Trusten Polk ( May 29 , 1811 -- April 16 , 1876 ) served as both the 12th Governor of Missouri in 1857 and U.S. Senator from 1857 to 1862 .
In Tam ( Khmer : អ៊ិន តាំ ; September 22 , 1922 -- April 1 , 2006 ) was a former Prime Minister of Cambodia .
Dadeus Grings ( born 7 September 1936 ) is a Roman Catholic bishop who is the current ordinary of the archdiocese of Porto Alegre .
Saint Carthage the Elder ( or Carthach ) was an Irish bishop and abbot in the sixth century .
Samuel Rinnah Van Sant ( May 11 , 1844 -- October 3 , 1936 ) was an American politician who served in the Minnesota House of Representatives and as the 15th Governor of Minnesota .
Horace Fairbanks ( March 21 , 1820 -- March 17 , 1888 ) was an American politician and the 36th Governor of Vermont from 1876 to 1878 .
Egon Vaupel ( born 15 November 1950 in Bad Endbach ) is a German politician , member of the SPD , and the incumbent mayor of Marburg .
Thomas Brassey , 1st Earl Brassey GCB TD JP DL ( 11 February 1836 -- 23 February 1918 ) , was a British Liberal Party politician , Governor of Victoria and founder of The Naval Annual .
Francesco Martelli was created cardinal priest in the consistory of 17 May 1706 by Pope Clement XI with the title of Sant'Eusebio .
Nancy Jenkins is a member of the Michigan House of Representatives from the 57th district , which covers most of Lenawee County , Michigan .
John of Basingstoke ( d. 1252 ) , also called John Basing was an Archdeacon of Leicester in the 13th century .
Hemming Andreas Carlgren ( born 8 July 1958 ) is a Swedish Centre Party politician , and a former Minister for the Environment in the Swedish government .
David Ralston is a Republican member of the Georgia House of Representatives for the 7th district , encompassing parts of Dawson County , Fannin County , and Gilmer County .
Isaac W. Patton was the 39th mayor of New Orleans ( November 18 , 1878 -- December 16 , 1880 ) .
George J. Woerth was a member of the Wisconsin State Assembly
Vincent Nguyen ( born Nguyễn Mạnh Hiếu on May 8 , 1966 ) is an auxiliary bishop of the Archdiocese of Toronto .
Curt Hagman ( born January 2 , 1965 ) was a Republican member of the California State Assembly , representing the 55th district .
Fernando Chui Sai On ( Chinese : 崔世安 ; pinyin : Cuī Shì'ān ; born 13 January 1957 ) is the current Chief Executive of Macau , he was the Secretary for Social and Cultural Affairs from 1999 to 2009 .
Andraos Abouna ( March 23 , 1943 -- July 27 , 2010 ) was the Roman Catholic auxiliary bishop of Hirta and the auxiliary bishop of the Chaldean Catholic Patriarchate of Babylon .
Veit Truchseß von Pommersfelden ( died 1503 ) was the Prince - Bishop of Bamberg from 1501 to 1503 .
Constantin Sănătescu ( January 14 , 1885 , Craiova -- November 8 , 1947 , Bucharest ) was a Romanian statesman who served as the first Prime Minister of Romania after the August 23 , 1944 coup , through which Romania left the Axis Powers and joined the Allies .
Vital I Michele ( or Vitale I Michiel ) ( died 1102 ) was a Doge of Venice ; he was the 33rd traditional ( 30th historic ) Doge of the Republic of Venice .
Evgeny Katichev is a professional ice hockey defenceman who currently a free agent .
Franz - Josef Vogt ( born 30 October 1985 ) is a retired international footballer from Liechtenstein who played as a defender .
Nick Niedert ( born June 16 , 1982 in Hudson , Iowa ) is an American professional ice hockey goaltender formerly of the Jersey Rockhoppers in the Eastern Professional Hockey League ( EPHL ) .

Charles Foster Kane is a fictional character and the subject of Orson Welles ' 1941 film Citizen Kane .

Vesper Lynd is a fictional character featured in Ian Fleming 's 1953 James Bond novel Casino Royale .
Stuart Neilson is a fictional character in the New Zealand soap opera Shortland Street who was portrayed by Martin Henderson as part of the original cast up until early 1995 .

The Eleven Kingdoms is a fictional collection of nations that serve as the primary setting of the Deryni novels of Katherine Kurtz .

Amy Shuard CBE ( 19 July 1924 -- 18 April 1975 ) was an English operatic soprano renowned in such dramatic roles as Elektra , Turandot and Brünnhilde .
Louis Musy ( born 22 October 1902 , Algeria , died 19 October 1981 ) was a French operatic baritone and stage director principally active at the Paris Opéra - Comique .
Marguerite Piazza ( May 6 , 1920 -- August 2 , 2012 ) was an American soprano , entertainer and philanthropist from New Orleans , Louisiana .
Peter Butterfield is a Canadian conductor and classical tenor .
William Matteuzzi ( born 12 December 1957 in Bologna , Italy ) is an Italian operatic tenor renowned for his impressive vocal range and prominent upper register , reaching a high F ( above the tenor high C ) in full voice , which enabled him to participate in the recent revival of the tenore contraltino repertoire .
Alexandra Deshorties ( born 1975 ) is a French - Canadian soprano who sings principally opera .
Nicolae Herlea ( 28 August 1927 -- February 24 , 2014 ) was a Romanian operatic baritone , particularly associated with the Italian repertory , especially the role of Rossini 's Figaro , which he sang around 550 times during his career .
James Campbell McInnes ( 23 January 1874 -- 8 February 1945 ) was a well - known English baritone singer and teacher at the turn of the 20th century , ex - husband of author Angela Thirkell and father of writer Colin MacInnes .
Anastasia Robinson ( c. 1692 -- April 1755 ) , later known as Anastasia , Countess of Peterborough , was an English soprano , later contralto , of the Baroque era .
Thorvald Lammers ( 15 January 1841 -- 8 February 1922 ) was a Norwegian baritone singer , choral conductor , composer , and biographer .
Cecilia Davies ( c. 1756 - 3 July 1836 ) was an English classical soprano who had an active international career in concerts and operas during the second half of the 18th century .
Sophie Diez or Dietz ( née Hartmann ) ( 1 September 1820 -- 3 May 1887 ) was a German soprano who sang leading roles with the Munich Hofoper ( now known as the Bavarian State Opera ) in a career spanning 40 years .
Allen Doone ( Edward Allen ) b. 3 Sep 1878 , Amboy , Lee , Illinois ( d. 4 May 1948 ) was an Irish - American tenor and comic who specialised in Irish romantic dramas .
Nadine Conner ( February 20 , 1907 - March 1 , 2003 ) was an American operatic soprano , radio singer and music teacher .
Anna Caterina Antonacci , ( born 5 April 1961 ) is an Italian soprano known for roles in the bel canto and Baroque repertories .
Iva Pacetti ( 13 December 1898 , Prato - 19 January 1981 , Milan ) was an Italian operatic soprano who had an active international career from 1920 - 1947 .
Roger Bourdin ( 14 June 1900 , Levallois - Perret - 14 September 1973 , Paris ) was a French baritone , particularly associated with the French repertory .
Jeanne Granier ( 31 March 1852 -- 18 or 19 December 1939 ) was a French soprano , born and died in Paris , whose career was centred on the French capital .
Otto Wiener ( February 13 , 1911 - August 5 , 2000 ) was an Austrian baritone , notable for his performances in the operas of Richard Wagner .
Heinrich Knote ( November 26 , 1870 -- January 15 , 1953 ) was an outstanding German dramatic tenor with an international reputation .
Franco Fagioli ( born 1981 in Tucumán ) is an Argentinan operatic countertenor .

Marie Hayward ( 1939 -- November 2011 ) was an English soprano , whose career was in opera in the UK and overseas and in concerts and recordings .
Heinrich Conrad Schleinitz ( * 1805 in Zechanitz for chub , † 1881 in Leipzig ) was a German jurist and tenor .
Maurice Stern ( Mauro Lampi ) is an American operatic tenor and sculptor , Stern graduated from the Eastman School of Music .

Stephanie Blythe ( born 1970 ) is an American mezzo - soprano who has had an active international career in operas and concerts since the early 1990s .
Basilio Basili ( March 21 , 1804 -- 1895 ) was an Italian tenor and composer .

John Boulter is a British tenor best known for his appearances as a soloist in the BBC 's long - running variety series The Black and White Minstrel Show .
Cristina Deutekom , also known as Christine Deutekom and Christina Deutekom ( 28 August 1931 -- 7 August 2014 ) , was a Dutch coloratura soprano opera singer .
Brendan O'Dowda ( 1 October 1925 -- 22 February 2002 ) was an Irish tenor who popularised the songs of Percy French .
Mariella Devia ( 12 April 1948 ) is an Italian operatic coloratura soprano , well known for performing many roles in the bel canto repertoire .
Ingeborg Reichelt ( born 11 May 1928 in Frankfurt an der Oder ) is a German soprano singer .
Regina Schörg is an Austrian soprano and teacher .
